<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#005B52" VLINK="#0D50A2" ALINK="#FFFFFF">

<BR>
<CENTER><H1>ERM Books</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=+1>Below is a list of the current books ERM offers.  To order, please complete the accompanying <A HREF="order.html"><B>Order Form</B></A>.
</FONT>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
<BR>
<BR>

<IMG SRC="/gif/haz.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Hazardous Waste Management</B></FONT>
<BR>
Michael D. LaGrega, Phillip L. Buckingham, Jeffrey C. Evans.
<BR>
1146 pages, hardcover, $64.00. 
<P>
Used in more than 130 college engineering programs today, this
 textbook provides a comprehensive overview of the eld, and
 of identification and management of hazardous wastes.
 Includes case studies, examples, and discussion topics and
 problems.<B> </B>Michael D. LaGrega has a Ph.D. in environmental
 engineering and is a principal of ERM in Exton, PA. He is also
 a professor and department head at Bucknell University.
 Phillip L. Buckingham has a master's degree in sanitary
 engineering and is a principal of ERM in Tampa, FL.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/inv.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Investors' Environmental Guidelines</B></FONT>
<BR> 
<KBD>Bulgaria, Czech Republic and Slovak Republic, Estonia,
Hungary, Latvia, Lithuania, Poland, Romania</KBD>
<BR>
Edited by the European Bank for Reconstruction and
<BR>
Development. 540 pages, softcover,$145.00.
<P>
Provides investors with a reference to environmental
 requirements of the central and local authorities in central
 and eastern European countries. Designed both for those
 with little knowledge of environmental requirements and for
 specialists. John Horberry, Ph.D., and Jill Shankleman,
 Ph.D., are principals and directors of ERM in London.
 Horberry's degree is in international environmental policy,
 Shankleman's degree is in sociology.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/ope_china.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Operating in China</B></FONT>
<BR><KBD>Pollution Control in the PRC: <BR>
Regulations and Reality</KBD>
<BR>
Shelly Clarke and ERM London.
<BR>
Distributed by ERM, 150 pages, softcover, $120.00.
<P>Provides investors with the basic regulations relating to
 commercial and industrial greenfield site developments,
 joint venture operations and company acquisitions in
 China. Focuses specifically on issues that arise from
 environmental protection measures and affect investments. Shelly Clarke is a senior consultant with
 ERM in Hong Kong.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/aud.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Auditing for Environmental Quality Leadership</B></FONT>
<BR>
<KBD>Beyond Compliance to Environmental Excellence</KBD>
<BR>
Edited by John T. Willig.
<BR>
331 pages, hardcover, $71.00. 
<P>
Covers the latest practices and shows, through specific case
 studies, how major corporations are applying them to achieve
 environmental excellence and competitive advantage. Covers
 major procedures used in defining, conducting, assessing and
 improving an environmental auditing program. Lawrence B.
 Cahill is a senior program director with ERM and also the
 author of <I>Environmental Audits</I>, which is now in its sixth edition;
 Randy A. Roig has a Ph.D. in physics and applied mathematics, and is a principal of ERM
 in Walnut Creek, CA; Peter Scheider has a master's degree in urban affairs and is a
 principal of ERM in Boston, MA.


<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/des.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Design and Operation of Activated Sludge Processes Using Respirometry</B></FONT>
<BR> 
Alan F. Rozich and Anthony F. Gaudy, Jr.
<BR>
189 pages, hardcover, $84.50
<P>
Presents practical information about implementation of water
-quality-based toxics control for wastewater treatment plants.
 Useful reference for wastewater treatment personnel,
 industrial wastewater treatment professionals, government
 agency regulators, environmental consultants and environmental attorneys. Al Rozich has a Ph.D. in
 environmental engineering from the University of Delaware.
 He is a licensed professional engineer and a principal of
 ERM in Exton, PA. 


<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/env.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Environmental Audits</B></FONT>
<BR>
<KBD>6th Edition</KBD>
<BR>
Lawrence B. Cahill, Editor, with Raymond W. Kane.
<BR>
560 pages, softcover, $98.00.
<P>Spans the range of relevant topics in environmental auditing,
 from new regulatory growth and enforcement data  to
 sample audit checklists. Lawrence Cahill has a master's
 degree in public administration and extensive audit
 experience. He is a senior program director with ERM in
 Exton, PA.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/mex.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Environmental Management for Mexican Industry</B></FONT>
<BR>
<KBD>Including Maquiladoras</KBD>
<BR>
Edited by ERM: Austin, Texas, and Mexico.
<BR>
210 pages, softcover, $395.00 per year (includes
 four updates*).
<P>
Provides an overview of Mexico's environmental problems and in-depth guidance on how
 industries should conduct business to comply with environmental regulations there. Mark C.
 Stuckey has a degree in chemical engineering and is an associate of ERM in Austin, TX.
 Fernando Ortiz Monasterio has degrees in industrial
 engineering and development planning and is the managing director for
 ERM in Mexico. <I>* Shipping and handling costs are not included for updates.</I>

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/bey.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Beyond Superfailure: America's Toxics Policy for the 1990s</B></FONT>
<BR> 
Daniel Mazmanian and David Morell.
<BR>
278 pages, softcover, $23.95.
<P>
Presents problems in managing hazardous wastes and
 other hazardous materials. Reviews lessons learned during
 the 1980s. Suggest approaches for positive action compliance, positive action cleanup, and positive action
 permitting. David Morell, Ph.D. is a principal of ERM in
 Walnut Creek, CA.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/gis.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Environmental GIS</B></FONT>
<BR><KBD>Applications to Industrial Facilities</KBD>
<BR>
William J. Douglas.
<BR>
128 pages, hardcover, $63.00.
<P>Describes application of information technology to address
 environmental, safety and health information management
 in order to assist industry in dealing with needs. William J.
 Douglas has a Ph.D. in engineering mechanics and was a
 senior program director with ERM Program Management
 Company, in Exton PA. 

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/imp.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Environmental Impact Assessment for Waste Treatment and Disposal
 Facilities</B></FONT>
<BR>
Judith Petts and Gev Eduljee.
<BR>
485 pages, hardcover, &#163; 39.95*.
<P>
Provides a unique, practical guide to the effective
 conduct of assessments specifically related to waste
 treatment and disposal facilities. A systematic approach integrating the technical, economic,
 social and environmental protection issues that govern the siting process and examining
 information and methodological requirements. <BR>
<I>* Shipping and handling costs are not included.</I>


<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/han.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>The Handbook of Environmentally Conscious Manufacturing</B></FONT>
<BR> 
<KBD> From Design &amp; production to labeling &amp; recycling
</KBD>
<BR>
Robert E. Cattanach, Jake M. Holdreith, Daniel P.
 Reinke, Larry K. Sibik.
<BR>
350 pages, hardcover, $75.00.
<P>
Integrates both the manufacturing and marketing dimensions of environmental
 excellence. A guide to creating an organization wide strategy for designing
 environmentally responsible products and methods, and using that same process to market them to
 the public. Daniel P. Reinke is a manager with ERM in
 the Eagan, MN, office.

<P>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>
<P>

<IMG SRC="/gif/fac.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=150>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Environmental Factoids</B> </FONT> <KBD>screen saver</KBD>
<BR>
$26.90 <I>(includes $6.95 shipping and handling)</I>
<BR>
To order: Contact CASCOM International at <BR>
800-889-0477.
<P>An educational screen saver for Windows that features 150 environmental trivia questions and
 answers presented against 16 colorful scenic backdrops. Developed by Anita Neidert, a project
 director at ERM in Kennesaw, GA, in conjunction with CASCOM International.

<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<BR>

