<HTML>

<HEAD>
        <TITLE>ERM Foundation</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#005b52" VLINK="#0d50a2" ALINK="#ffffff" BACKGROUND="/gif/ermbg5.gif">

<P>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/jpeg/foundation.jpg" BORDER="0" HEIGHT="167" WIDTH="500" ALIGN=bottom> 
</CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE=+2>

ERM has a long tradition of contributing to and participating in philanthropic endeavors, including educational programs and projects to improve living conditions in communities.  

</FONT>
<p>
<B>Mission Statement</B>

<P>

The ERM Foundation is a not for profit organization whose mission is to provide human resources and/or financial assistance to projects that contribute to the improvement of the earth's environment, quality of life and sustainable development throughout the world through appropriate charitable, educational, and scientific endeavors.


<hr>
<B><A HREF="projects.html">Projects for ERM Foundation</A></B>
<hr>


<B>To Make a Contribution</B>
<P>


Help us to expand our efforts to benefit others.  Please get involved and become part of this effort of making the world better for everyone.  Contribute by making checks payable to:  
<p>


The ERM Foundation, 855 Springdale Drive, Exton, Pennsylvania 19341-2859.
<p>
For more information on making contributions, contact Jack Newell (610) 524-3500.


<HR>

<B> To Make a Grant Application </B>
<P>


The selection criteria for grants is as follows:


<p>
<ul>
<li>	The project will make a significant (observable) difference in the

	environment and/or quality of life.


<p>
<li>	The project provides an opportunity for participation by ERM Group

	staff as well as monetary contribution.


<p>
<li>	The project funding will generally range from $5,000 to $100,000.


<p>
<li>	It is desirable that the project should be deductible under the U.S. Tax Code.


<p>
<li>	The project should have an educational component related to the environment, health or safety.


<p>
<li>	The project should ideally be able to leverage matching funds.

<p>
<li>	The project should have a means to continue to be maintained on its own after the award funding is expended.


<p>
<li>	The project should provide an opportunity for donor recognition.

<p>
</ul>
The ERM Foundation solicits proposals during the summer months with all applications required to be submitted by 15 July.  Selected proposals will be funded by year-end.  For more information, contact Judy Hushon (703) 734-9327.


<p>
For general information about the ERM Foundation, contact John McGlennon, ERM, Boston, MA (617) 742-8228.
<p>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<p>
