<HEAD>
<TITLE>Site Remediation - Regulatory Alerts</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Jamie O'Keefe,  9-Jul-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Salman Sajid, 10-Jul-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Martin Schamis, 10-Jul-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#3300CC" VLINK="#003B32" ALINK="#FFFFFF">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=6>
<TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=top WIDTH=250>

<H1>Site Remediation</H1>
<FONT SIZE=+1>regulatory alerts</FONT>

</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=2
<P>
Since the U.S. Congress defeat of the Superfund reauthorization, not much activity has taken place in the site remediation regulatory area until recently with the proposed Hazardous Waste Identification Rule (HWIR).  ERM has developed summaries of the HWIR and other RCRA compliance regulations that you can view from the following list.
<P>
<A HREF="CFR_261.html">HWIR 40 CFR 261 (Summary)</A>
<p>
<A HREF="">HWIR (Regulatory Review)</A>
<p>
<A HREF="">HWIR Exit Levels</A>
<p>
<A HREF="">Procedures to Submit and Support an HWIR Exemption Claim</A>
<p>
<A HREF="40CFR-29.html">HWIR Contaminated Media 40 CFR 269</A>
<p>
<A HREF="RCRA_tanks.html">Air Emissions Standard for RCRA Tanks, Surface Impoundments, and Containers (Subpart CC) 40 CFR 264, 265</A>
<p>
<A HREF="phase3.html">Phase III Land Disposal Restriction (LDR) Rule</A>
<p>
<A HREF="phase4.html">Phase IV LDR 40 CFR 268</A>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P
<BR>
<p>
