<HEAD>
<TITLE>Air Quality - Regulatory Alerts</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Jamie O'Keefe,  9-Jul-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Salman Sajid, 10-Jul-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Martin Schamis, 10-Sep-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#3300CC" VLINK="#003B32" ALINK="#FFFFFF">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=6>
<TR><TD VALIGN=top WIDTH=250>

<H1>Air Quality</H1>
<FONT SIZE=+1>regulatory alerts</FONT>

</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=2>
<P>
Since the promulgation of the Clean Air Act Amendments (CAAA) in 1990, considered the most significant piece of legislation ever enacted, the area of air quality compliance has seen more activity than any other regulatory issue.  The CAAA Title V Operating Permit requirements are unprecedented in the compliance arena.  Also, the RMP under 112(r) is an applicability that should not be overlooked.  Listed below are recent air quality regulatory alerts developed by ERM.

<p>
<A HREF="70021.html">NJDEP DER Open Market Trading Program</A>
<P>
<A HREF="acc_release.html">EPA's Accidental Release Prevention Requirements: Risk Management Programs Under Clean Air Act Section 112(r)(7)</A>
<p>
<A HREF="chrome_MACT.html">Chromium Plating MACT Requirements</A>
<p>
<A HREF="op_permit.html">Pennsylvania's State Operating Permit Program</A>
<p>
<A HREF="airquality.html">Allegheny County's Minor Source Operating Permit Program</A>
<p>
<A HREF="DE_hosp.html">Delaware's Title V Program Impacts Hospitals</A>
<p>
<A HREF="ohio_title5.html">Ohio's Title V program</A>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P
<BR>
<p>
