<HEAD>
<TITLE>Health and Safety - Regulatory Alerts</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Jamie O'Keefe,  9-Jul-1996 -->
<!-- Changed by: Martin Schamis, 15-Jul-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#3300CC" VLINK="#003B32" ALINK="#FFFFFF">

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=6 CELLPADDING=6>
<TR><TD VALIGN=top WIDTH=250>

<H1>Health and Safety</H1>
<FONT SIZE=+1>regulatory alerts</FONT>

</TD>
<TD ROWSPAN=2>
<P>
Impending OSHA budget cuts and reductions in the staff of regulatory officers have given some industry professionals the misconceived notion that they can be lax in the area of health and safety compliance.<BR>
<B>Warning:</B>The OSHA Process Safety Management (PSM) Rule is not an issue to be ignored.  If applicable, compliance to PSM is imperative; otherwise, a facility can be faced with large penalties if it is found negligent in its effort to comply.  Link yourself to ERM's PSM regulatory alert below to find out more about this high impacting rule.
<P>
<A HREF="PSM_alert.html">Process Safety Management</A>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P
<BR>
