<HEAD>
    <TITLE>A*I*M*S - Title V</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff" background="ermembose.jpg"><table><tr><td valign=center><a href="http://www.erm.com"><IMG SRC="erm.gif" border=0 width=80></a></td><td><center><img src="panel.jpg"><br>
<img src="header1.gif"><br><font size=+1>Electronic Information Management For Title V Air Quality Compliance.</font size></center><br></td></tr></table>

<table cellpadding=2><tr><td valign=top>
<A HREF="advantage.html"><img src="adv.jpg" border=0></a><br>
<A HREF="overview.html"><img src="over.jpg" border=0></a><br>
<A HREF="main.html"><img src="demo.jpg" border=0></a><br>
<A HREF="white.html"><img src="white.jpg" border=0><br>
<A HREF="http://www.erm.com/library/resources/18_3/paper.html"><img src="facility.jpg" border=0></a>
<A HREF="feedback.html"><img src="contact.jpg" border=0></a>
</td><td><h5>Managing compliance with air pollution regulations, 
particularly the Title V/ Part '70 Operating Permit Program, is 
now more challenging and information- intensive than ever.  
A*I*M*S-Title V is a software tool developed by ERM to assist 
facilities with Title V compliance and is based on our nationwide 
Title V permitting and air compliance management experience. 
<P>
An un-compiled Microsoft Access&#174; 2.0 relational database, 
A*I*M*S-Title V stresses flexibility and openness; connectivity 
with existing electronic data; rapid customization to individual 
State Title V programs; and management of ongoing compliance needs.  
We invite you to explore our site to see our unique approach and to 
preview our system.  Please contact us via 
<a href="mailto:charlier@logical.net">e-mail</a> 
or telephone at (518) 452-4291 for more information. </h5></tr></table><CENTER></CENTER>


