<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Alert</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Salman Sajid, 10-Jul-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BR>
<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3> 
<CENTER>AFC Technology for
High-Strength Organic Waste and Sludge Streams</CENTER> 
</H3>
<p>

<IMG LOWSRC="/gif/afc_lo.gif" SRC="/gif/afc_hi.gif" ALIGN=LEFT>
<B>Description</B>
<p>
The patented Advanced Fluidized Composting (AFC) Technology represents the state-of-the art in process stream treatment.  A proprietary combination of thermophilic biological treatment with a chemical treatment step enables AFC technology to treat highly concentrated organic waste and/or  sludge streams efficiently and with only a fraction of the residual sludge generated in other aerobic and anaerobic biological processes.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<ul>
<B>Features</B>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Able to withstand high COD loadings 
(5,000 to 60,000+ ppm)                          
<p>
<li>Sustained operating temperatures of 40 
to 70C 
<p>
<li>Effective with high TDS streams
<p>
<li>High rates of organic destruction
<p>
</ul>
<B>Benefits</B>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Cost effective
<p>
<li>Excellent system stability
<p>
<li>Effect good biological treatment in low ambient temperature conditions
<p>
<li>Minimal sludge disposal cost
<P>
</ul>
<B>Areas of Application</B>
<p>
<ul>
<li>Sludge treatment and reduction
<p>
<li>High-strength waste treatment
<p>
<li>Waste minimization
<p>
<li>Solid waste treatment
<p>
<li>Bioremediation
<p>
<li>Source treatment
<p>
</ul>
<B>Notable Projects</B>
<p>
<ul>
<li>High-strength organic acids e.g., salicyclic and acetic
<p>
<li>Fermentation broths
<p>
<li>Solvents
<p>
<li>Viscose fiber sludge
<p>
<li>Waste activated sludge (pharmaceutical, chemical, plastic, and food)
<p>
<li>High-strength methanol streams
<p>
<li>Phenolic waste streams
<p>
<li>Cosmetic-fats, oil and grease (FOG) wastes
<p>
<li>Metal stamping and caustic wastes
<p>
</ul>
<B>For more information, contact:
</B><BR>
Alan F. Rozich, Ph.D., P.E., DEE<BR>
(610) 524-3893
<P>

</ul>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
<IMG SRC="/gif/button_bar.gif" WIDTH=484 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ISMAP USEMAP="#buttonbar"></a>
</center>
