<Body Bgcolor="#Ffffff" Link="#005b52" Vlink="#0d50a2" Alink="#Ffffff"> 
<BR>
<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><H1>The ERMethod II</H1>
<H2>A New Technology for Contaminated Sites</H2></CENTER>
<HR NOSHADE>
<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
The ERMethod II, an Earth Renovation Method developed by the Environmental Resources Management Group, provides containment and eliminates contact between contaminated soils and ground water.  The ERMethod II is particularly cost effective at sites where ground water is in contact with contaminated soils, and where dealing with ground water is costly and/or time-consuming.
<BR>
<!-- Insert Image here -->
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<CENTER>
The ERMethod II is an in-situ remediation technique that saves time and money.
<BR>
ERMethod II PLUS incorporates in-situ treatment methods such as bioremediation and air stripping.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>
For more information about ERMethod II and ERMethod II PLUS, please contact the professionals at Environmental Resources Management.
</B>
</FONT>
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="/gif/LOGO_ERM.gif">
</CENTER>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
