<HTML>
<TITLE> ERM FAST Field Analytical Services Real-Time Solutions</TITLE>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><H1>ERM FAST Field Analytical Services Real-Time Solutions</H1></CENTER>
<p>
<BR>
<BR>
ERM offers mobile field analytical services to help our clients meet demanding deadlines.  The ERM-FAST service provides high quality screening or laboratory grade results in the field.  By providing immediate and accurate field data, ERM-FAST reduces the time and costs associated with site investigation or remedial efforts.
<p>
The ERM-FAST service:
<ul>
<li>	Provides real-time screening data and laboratory-grade results
<li>	Reduces total project costs
<li>	Reduces total project time
<li>	Focuses investigations (drilling and sampling efforts)
<li>	Monitors remedial efforts
<li>	Protects sampling personnel
<li>	Produces high-quality defensible data
</ul>
The ERM-FAST service is a powerful tool for complete and cost-effective on-site sampling efforts as part of environmental investigations and remedial programs.  This analytical service assesses and analyzes on-site releases faster and less expensively than multiple analyses performed in a fixed-based laboratory.  The ERM-FAST service can be set up at a client's facility, in a standard construction trailer or in our specially-equipped vehicles including four-wheel-drive vans to travel to areas of a site that may be inaccessible to conventional vehicles.
<p>
The service is equipped with state-of-the-art analytical equipment including:
<ul>
<li>	Gas chromatograph/mas spectrometers (GC/MS)
<li>	Gas chromatograph/photo-ionization detectors (GC/PID)
<li>	Gas chromatograph/electron capture detectors (GC/ECD)
<li>	X-ray fluorescence units (XRF)
</ul>
With this equipment, ERM-FAST can detect virtually all of the organic compounds listed on the priority pollutants list and target compound list, and most target analyte list or priority pollutant list metals.
<p>
ERM's analytical instruments are configured for mobile field use, yet can detect and quantify in the low parts-per-million or parts-per-billion ranges for waters, solids and wastes.
<p>
<H2>Expertise in the Field</H2>
<p>
Experienced professionals at ERM apply innovative technologies to solve a wide range of environmental problems.  The ERM-FAST staff includes field chemists and scientists who have designed and implemented field screening and analytical programs to meet the specific needs of hundreds of clients.  Programs are designed based on information available, on-site operations or prior laboratory analysis.  We will prepare site-specific standards for the analyses to be performed while allowing for adjustment of parameters in the field to ensure that the data collected meets the requirements of the project.  The ability to adjust methods used based on results from the field realizes time and cost savings for the client.
<p>
<H2>Fixed-Based Laboratory Services</H2>
<p>
The ERM-FAST service also provides fixed-based laboratory services for rapid sample analysis.  This service can be used in conjunction with the ERM-FAST mobile field units to expedite specific project objective or as an alternative to field analysis.  The ERM-FAST staff used the laboratory to design custom analytical procedures based on specific client requirements.  Field analytical methods are tested in the lab before they are used.  This ensures the accuracy of the techniques and reduces times and costs in the field.
<p>
For more information about ERM-FAST service, please call 800-544-3117 or e-mail mkt_info@erm.com.

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BODY>
</HTML>
