<H3>

<!-- heading -->
ERM RANKED 17th LARGEST HAZARDOUS WASTE
CONTRACTOR IN ENR TOP 20 LISTINGS

</H3>

<!-- text -->
EXTON, Pa. -- May 24, 1996 -- The Environmental Resources Management (ERM) Group was once again ranked as the 17th largest hazardous waste contractor in a list of the Top 20 hazardous waste contractor market leaders, according to the <I>Engineering News-Record (ENR) Top 400 Contractors</I> listing recently released.  
<p>	For contractors in all markets, ERM ranked 385th in construction revenues for 1995.  The rankings are based on construction revenues for last year, which totaled $55.2-million for ERM.  
<p>	Industry analysts characterized 1995 as a year when environmental remediation and construction markets were significantly growing, nearly 11 percent over the previous year.  Said Jack C. Newell, an ERM principal, "We continue to see a number of environmental cleanup projects moving from the assessment and engineering phase into site remediation work.  This includes work from the private sector, U.S. Department of Defense projects, as well as an increasing amount of international work."
<p>	ERM's total revenues increased nine percent to $283-million for fiscal year 1996 (ending March 31, 1996), compared to the previous year.  The company expects another year of growth and anticipates that its business will reach approximately $300-million by the end of fiscal year 1997, according to Newell.  <I>ENR</I> previously reported ERM's growth when it announced that ERM had moved up from #27 to #25 of the Top 500  architectural/
engineering firms in the United States.  

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<H6>
ERM Group is a global consulting organization of 2,400 environmental, health and safety specialists at more than 90 locations in 24 countries.  The firm is one of the world's largest providers of environmental consulting and engineering services to industry, and offers air quality, wastewater, hazardous and solid waste management; site assessment and remediation; human health and ecological risk assessment; process safety; management consulting; information management; analytical laboratory services and turnkey construction.
</H6>
