<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>

PANZARDI-ERM FORMED IN PUERTO RICO; ERM EXPANDS PRESENCE IN CARIBBEAN<P>

</H3>

SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico - October 25, 1996 - Pedro Panzardi &
Associates (PPA) of San Juan, Puerto Rico, has joined Environmental Resources
Management (ERM), an international environmental, health and safety (EHS)
consulting firm.  The new firm, which is operating as Panzardi-ERM, Inc.,
expands ERM's presence in Puerto Rico and the Caribbean.  <p>
PPA, founded in Puerto Rico in 1986 by Pedro J. Panzardi, is a process,
environmental and U.S. FDA regulatory compliance consulting firm. 
"Formation of Panzardi-ERM is an important part of ERM's global
growth strategy to expand its services in Puerto Rico and the Caribbean to serve
its multinational clients who have a number of facilities there," says Paul H.
Woodruff, ERM chairman, CEO and founder.  "Additionally, Panzardi &
Associates have a strong expertise in FDA regulatory compliance work that will
expand by providing this service to ERM's worldwide pharmaceutical clients." 
Pedro J. Panzardi, president of Panzardi-ERM, remarks:  "We have one
of the largest, if not <I>the</I> largest, staff of any consulting firm in Latin America
dedicated specifically to the pharmaceutical, beverage, chemical, food processing
and electronic industries."  The company has international experience and has
worked in Cuba (for the UN Development Program), Dominican Republic,
Colombia, Costa Rica, Jamaica and the British Virgin islands. <P>
Panzardi-ERM has a bilingual staff of more than 20 qualified personnel
who offer combined experience in all areas of process, environmental and project
engineering from developing feasibility studies, assessments, and project
concepts to final engineering drawings and specifications; as well as cost
estimates, construction supervision, startup, operational assistance, training,
validation, and operation and maintenance.  <p>
A recognized leader in environmental technology, Pedro Panzardi
introduced the first Rotary Biological Contactor (RBC) and Sequencing Batch
Reactor (SBR) in Puerto Rico.  He is also responsible for the first known
application of SBR to pharmaceutical process wastewaters in the United States. 
Panzardi's expertise in environmental engineering is well established.  He
has built a successful career in technical management and process  engineering in
the pharmaceutical industry since he first started working at Eli-Lilly Industries in
1970.  Panzardi has 26 years of experience in environmental and process
engineering consulting work in Puerto Rico, much of it for pharmaceutical
companies.  <p>
Born in New York City, Panzardi attended elementary school in
Paterson, New Jersey, before his family relocated to Puerto Rico.  He holds a
B.S. degree in Chemical Engineering from the University of Puerto Rico and a
Masters degree in Environmental Engineering from Rensselaer Polytechnic
Institute.  Panzardi is a Registered Professional Engineer in Puerto Rico and
Florida.  <p>
Panzardi has received Certificates of Accomplishment from the
Environmental Quality Board and the Puerto Rico Manufacturer's Association in
1978, 1979 and 1980 for environmental control excellence in industry.  He
served as both vice president and president of the Institute of Chemical Engineers
of Puerto Rico from 1980 to 1982.  The Institute of Chemical Engineers named
him Distinguished Chemical Engineer for 1994.   <P>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
