<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>

<!-- heading -->
ERM MITCHELL MCCOTTER EXPANDS IN AUSTRALIA;
ADDS NEW OFFICE, RISK MANAGEMENT SERVICES


</H3>

<!-- text -->
SYDNEY, Australia - June 14, 1996 -- ERM Mitchell McCotter & Associates Pty. Ltd., the Australian member of the Environmental Resources Management (ERM) Group, has added a sixth office in Australia near Melbourne, in Jolimont, Victoria.  Graeme Dickson has been named regional manager of the Melbourne office.  
<p>	Additionally, the firm has strengthened its risk management consulting services in Australia through Four Elements, the risk assessment and management arm of ERM.  Praneet Mehra has been appointed risk assessment specialist for ERM Mitchell McCotter/Four Elements and will be based in the Sydney office.  
<p>	The Melbourne office becomes ERM's sixth office in Australia; the others are in Sydney, New South Wales; Brisbane, Queensland; Maitland, New South Wales; Perth, Western Australia; and Taree, northern New South Wales.  ERM Mitchell McCotter now employs more than 100 people throughout Australia.  
<p>	"The new office and expanded services are important components of ERM's global growth strategy and continued expansion in the growing Asia-Pacific area," says Paul H. Woodruff, ERM founder and chief executive officer.  "ERM Mitchell McCotter is one of the largest environmental consulting firms in Australia and offers a full range of services in environmental engineering and audits, environmental studies, sociological and economic investigations, and urban and regional planning."  
<p>	"We have been expanding our work in the Melbourne area and throughout Victoria.  The new office and risk management services add to the strength of our organization, allowing us to broaden our services with a local office at which the full range of ERM services will be available," remarks Paul Mitchell, cofounder of ERM Mitchell McCotter.  
<p>	Graeme Dickson has 20 years of consulting experience and an extensive knowledge of planning legislation, policy and development issues.  He has worked throughout metropolitan and rural Victoria and consulted on major development projects in the recreational, residential and commercial sectors.  His experience included the preparation of planning strategies in the northern and southeastern growth corridors of Melbourne.  
<p>	Praneet Mehra will provide risk and hazards consulting, risk management, quantitative risk assessments, hazard and operability studies, and safety audits for clients in government and industry.  He has conducted and managed many risk assessment studies throughout Australia for onshore oil and gas facilities, road transport of hazardous goods, railway operations, sewage treatment facilities, and power distribution.  Mehra is a mechanical engineer with a broad background in the chemical industry.  
<p>	ERM is a global consulting organization of more than 2,400 environmental, health and safety specialists at more than 95 locations in 24 countries.  The firm is one of the world's largest providers of environmental consulting and engineering services to industry, and offers air quality, wastewater, hazardous and solid waste management; site assessment and remediation; human health and ecological risk assessment; process safety; management consulting; information management; analytical laboratory services and turnkey construction.  


</BLOCKQUOTE>
</TD></TR>
