<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>

NJDEP AWARDS LABORATORY CERTIFICATION FOR ERM-FAST&reg; SERVICE <P>
</H3>

 EXTON, Pa. -- November 13, 1996 -- The New Jersey Department of
Environmental Protection (NJDEP) has awarded laboratory certification to
Environmental Resources Management (ERM) for its ERM-FAST&reg; environ
mental laboratory analysis service.  To receive certification, ERM successfully
met the stringent criteria established by the state of New Jersey.  These included
the analysis of performance evaluation samples, facility audits and quality
assurance documentation review.  ERM is a leading global environmental, health
and safety consulting firm.  <p>
     "The NJDEP certification attests to the proficiency and competency of
ERM-FAST's environmental analytical capabilities," according to William
Goldschmidt, ERM-FAST business manager in Exton.  "This level of recognized
proficiency and expertise is important to industrial companies and regulatory
agencies that are selecting an environmental laboratory for project analytical
support."  <p>
     ERM-FAST provides both mobile and fixed-base laboratory analytical
services from its operating bases in Exton, Pennsylvania and Los Alamos, New
Mexico.  "The service has been providing critical and cost effective analytical
support since 1990 for a wide variety of environmental site investigation and
remediation projects from the screening level through fully approved regulatory
methods," says Goldschmidt.<p>
     To meet the need for rapid analytical results, ERM offers the alternative of
on-site analysis of wastes through its Field Analytical Services Technology
(ERM-FAST).  This service consists of fully self-supported, mobile field   <p>
screening units which bring laboratory quality, instrumentation, methods and
degreed chemists to the field to provide real-time analytical results, he explains.
     For more information about ERM-FAST's capabilities and analytical
service, contact Bill Goldschmidt at (610) 524-3518.  <p>


</TD></TR>
