<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>

<!-- heading -->
LITERATURE PRESENTS OPPORTUNITIES IN
BROWNFIELDS

</H3>

<!-- text -->
EXTON, Pa. -- June 21, 1996 -- New literature entitled "<I>Brownfields: New Approaches to Asset Management</I>" is now available from the Environmental Resources Management (ERM) Group.  The literature identifies why brownfields programs are emerging, how they work, why they represent a major opportunity for business and - most important - who can benefit from brownfields now.
<p>	"Brownfields" are abandoned, idled or underused industrial and commercial facilities where expansion or redevelopment is complicated by real or perceived environmental contamination.  Brownfields programs are new approaches to site assessment and clean-up designed to encourage redevelopment of brownfields sites while still protecting health and the environment.
<p>	To obtain a copy of <I>Brownfields: New Approaches to Asset Management</I>, contact Gregory Lloyd, Marketing Communications Department, ERM Group, 855 Springdale Drive, Exton, PA  19341, at 800-544-3117 or fax 610-524-3866.


</BLOCKQUOTE>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<H6>
ERM Group is a global consulting organization of 2,400 environmental, health and safety specialists at more than 90 locations in 24 countries.  The firm is one of the world's largest providers of environmental consulting and engineering services to industry, and offers air quality, wastewater, hazardous and solid waste management; site assessment and remediation; human health and ecological risk assessment; process safety; management consulting; information management; analytical laboratory services and turnkey construction.
</H6>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
<IMG SRC="/gif/button_bar.gif" WIDTH=484 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ISMAP USEMAP="#buttonbar"></a>
</center>
