<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Letter from the President</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Martin Schamis,  9-Aug-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/president.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B><FONT SIZE="+3">G</FONT><FONT SIZE="+1">REETINGS.</FONT></B>  This is the first ERM Group Annual Report.  It has been prepared primarily for our 274 shareholders; however, we also hope it will be of value to our employees, strategic partners, suppliers, clients and prospective clients.  It contains an overview of ERM's operations for the year, highlighting our wide variety of clients, the services we offer, their geographic distribution and our financial performance. <P>
Financially, 1996 was a good year.  ERM remains at or near the top of the industry in terms of revenues and profits.  Gross revenue grew by three percent in 1996 to $283 million.   According to <I>Engineering News
Record (ENR)</I>, we advanced from the 27th largest consulting engineering firm to the 25th, with most of our growth coming from the Asia/Pacific, South American and European segments of our business.  Profit margins remained high with increases in Europe and Asia/Pacific offsetting a slight decline in North America. <P>
It is clear that the environmental consulting industry is in a worldwide transition that began in the early 1990s.  Some traditional service sectors are maturing particularly in the U.S. and in parts of Western Europe and Australia.  However, new opportunities are arising as increasing emphasis is placed on improving our environment.  In Asia, Central America and South America, there is growing demand for many of our services.  Our clients also have become more sophisticated and discerning with respect to value.  Many are concerned with sustainable development and are looking to compete in an environmentally responsible way.  They also are embracing global, independently certifiable standards for quality and performance, and they expect their suppliers to do so.  It is important to recognize that even in the markets where we are most established and are the most mature, we have less than a five percent share.  That means there is plenty of opportunity for growth by adapting our capabilities to serve clients in more creative and value added ways.  <P>
We started two businesses last year and opened several new offices.   The new businesses are Fusion Staffing Services, which offers temporary and permanent staff to the environmental industry, and the Strategic Chemical Management Group, which reduces costs and environmental concerns for clients by arranging strategic sourcing of chemicals  and services through vendor alliances.  Our new offices are in China, India, Australia, Germany, Mexico, the U.S. and Chile.<P>
We have begun ISO certification for all ERM offices.  It has been achieved in several locations worldwide, and we expect the rest of our offices to be certified by the end of 1997.<P>
Last year we took an important step forward in assessing what lies ahead in the global environmental market by initiating a major strategic planning process, which we called "Vision 2000".  Every company within the ERM Group was involved in establishing goals for our businesses worldwide and in determining the strategies we are going to adopt to achieve those goals over the next five years.<P>
Fundamental to the success of our strategy are the values that we have always considered  important.  The changes in the environmental market today reaffirm that the values we have emphasized since ERM's inception are the correct ones &#139; and we plan to stay with them.  They include:<P>
<ul> 
     <li>employee ownership<P>
     <li>decentralized and empowered management<P>
     <li>an entrepreneurial culture<P>
     <li>investing in technology<P>
     <li>offering clients a full range of services from a single source<P>
     <li>developing new services to meet changing client needs<P>
     <li>providing service globally <P>
     <li>emphasizing quality and service<P>
</ul>

Vision, core values and a market-driven strategy are only part of the reason for ERM's success.  The other crucial element is our people - and we have some of the best in the world.  I want to thank all our employees, managers and shareholders who worked hard last year to serve our clients with creativity and dedication.  Judging from the satisfaction expressed by many of our clients, all of you deserve credit for frequently exceeding their expectations.<P>
We can say with assurance that we are one of the world's leading environmental
occupational health and safety consulting groups.  We have a lead, but we must not be complacent.  We need to ensure our clients benefit from our collective skills and experience by continuing to improve our ability to work as a team. We must continue to work intelligently, creatively and with dedication to give our clients what they deserve - the very best in service and value.<P>
<BR>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>      
<ul> 
                       Sincerely,<P>
Paul H. Woodruff<br>
President and CEO<BR>
                              The ERM Group<BR>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>      
</ul> 

</BLOCKQUOTE>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
