<HEAD>
<TITLE>Global Overview</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Martin Schamis,  2-Aug-1996 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H2>Global Overview</H2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE="+3">A</FONT>s environmental managers, consultants, engineers and scientists, ERM carries out assignments throughout the world as unique and diverse as our growing client base.  At any time during the past year, several thousand projects were underway for a broad range of companies and governmental organizations.  Since ERM was founded, we have completed projects in more than 160 countries and for almost every industry sector from chemical manufacturing to transport engineering.<P>
This section of the Annual Report shows the scope and variety of projects during
fiscal year 1996; from analyzing the waste management needs of Hong Kong in the next century, to transforming a contaminated rail yard in Sacramento, California into houses, shops and offices, to helping the U.K. Department of Trade and Industry assess the impact of potential legislation on industry.<P>
ERM has grown by adapting to changes in the global environmental marketplace
We expect to continue to grow in the years ahead by serving the rapidly developing economies in Asia and South America, and by meeting the demands of the more mature markets in Europe and North America.  Our success is a result of our 
commitment to serving our clients responsively and well. As we move into the larger, more competitive environmental market of the twenty-first century, that commitment remains our top concern.<P>
