<HEAD>
<TITLE>Feature Office</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/gif/ermbgnew.gif">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="/gif/ftrhead.gif" WIDTH="445" HEIGHT="68" ALIGN=bottom
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/jpeg/pedro.jpeg" align=left hspace=10> Panzardi-ERM, Inc,.<BR>
97 De Diego Avenue<BR>
San Francisco<BR>
Rio Pedras, PR 00926<BR>
(787) 765-0808 (phone)<BR>
(787) 765-1262 (fax)<BR>
<p>
ERM expands our presence in the Caribbean with the opening of Panzardi-ERM, Inc., in San Juan, Puerto Rico - our 100th location.  Founded as Pedro Panzardi & Associates in 1986, the firm will specialize in process, environmental and US FDA regulatory compliance consulting.
<p>
Pedro J. Panzardi is founder and president of ERM's new office.  The company has international experience and has worked in Cuba (for the UN Development Program), Dominican Republic, Colombia, Costa Rico, Jamaica and the British Virgin Islands.
<p>
Panzardi-ERM has a bilingual staff of more that 20 qualified personnel who offer combined experience in all areas of process, environmental and project engineering from developing feasibility studies, assessments, and project concepts to final engineering drawings and specifications; as well as cost estimates, construction supervision, startup, operational assistance, training, validation and operation and maintenance.
<p>
Panzardi is a recognized leader in environmental technology, having introduced the first Rotary Biological Contractor and Sequencing Batch Reactor (SBR) in Puerto Rico.  He is also responsible for the first known application of SBR to pharmaceutical process wastewaters in the United States.  He has more than 26 years of experience in environmental consulting.
<p>

