</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Alert</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H3> 
Air Emission Standard for RCRA Tanks,
Surface Impoundments, and Containers (Subpart CC)
40 CFR 264, 265
</H3>
<I> Action: </I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> Promulgated Rule </FONT><BR>
<I> Date: </I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> Published December 6, 1994, F.R. 62896 </FONT><BR>
<I> For More Information Contact: </I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> Richard J. Dulcey<br>
610-524-3610 </FONT><BR>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD>Introduction</KBD></FONT>
<P>



The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (USEPA) issued Subpart CC which will regulate organic air emissions from tanks, surface impoundments, and containers.  The rule potentially affects any facility that currently generates or manages organic containing hazardous wastes, including less than 90-day storage areas at large quantity generators.  The applicability threshold is whether a hazardous waste contains greater than 100 ppm (by weight) of volatile organic compounds.  EPA has specified several new test methods for determining the VOC content.  Each facility is required to make an initial waste determination, which includes multiple samples, however, averaging of results is allowed over time.  
<p>
Affected facilities are required to either: 1) develop a storage system which meets an exemption; 2) implement specified storage methods or uses certain containers; or 3) install controls which provide to 95% removal.  The compliance date has been postponed by EPA to June 5, 1996.  If the air emission control requirements cannot be put into operation by June 5, 1996, then the facility must provide an implementation schedule by then with the ultimate deadline being December 8, 1997.
<p>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> ERM Can Help </KBD></FONT>
<P>


Environmental Resources Management (ERM), Inc. can put our expertise to work for you in the following areas.
<p>
<ul>
<li>Review your current storage and management practices and recommend approaches to use the available exemptions and minimize the rules impact.
<p>
<li>Develop a sampling and analysis plan, and assess what physical and operational changes may be required to comply with the storage requirements.
<p>
<li>Provide engineering services to design, construct, and operate air emission control equipment.
<p>
</ul>
If you need assistance in any of these areas, or with other environmental challenges, call Rich Dulcey at (610) 524-3610 in Exton, PA.
<p>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> Key Features: </KBD></FONT>
<p>

<ul>
<li>Establishes air emission controls on hazardous wastes containing >100 ppmw VOC.
<p>
<li>Applies to Permitted, Interim Status, and Large Quantity Generator facilities.
<p>
<li>Exemption allowed for wastes containing an average VOC concentration of <100 ppmw at the point of generation, or wastes treated to remove the organics to equivalent levels.
<p>
<li>Requires specific sampling of each wastestream, and allows averaging periods for results up to one year.
<p>
<li>Requires regular monitoring of affected units and leak monitoring using Method 21.
<p>
<li>Waste determinations have to be made at least once per year and when there are changes to the waste stream.
</ul>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
<IMG SRC="/gif/button_bar.gif" WIDTH=484 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ISMAP USEMAP="#buttonbar"></a>
</center>
<br>



<MAP NAME="buttonbar">
<AREA SHAPE=rect COORDS="0,0,81,34" HREF="/">
<AREA SHAPE=rect COORDS="81,0,162,34" HREF="/comment/">
<AREA SHAPE=rect COORDS="162,0,243,34" HREF="/search/iaquery/">
<AREA SHAPE=rect COORDS="243,0,324,34" HREF="/library/">
