<HEAD>
<TITLE>Alert</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H3>

Phase IV LDR 40 CFR 268 

</H3>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD>Introduction</KBD></FONT>
<P>

The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (USEPA) has proposed the final portion of the Land Disposal Restrictions program.  The major elements of this Phase IV proposal would regulate cross-media contaminant transport from Subtitle D surface impoundments due to air, water, or solids releases.  The rule would also establish treatment standards for sludge containing hazardous constituents in those impoundments.  In general, this proposal would apply to any clean water act systems which are managing ignitable, corrosive, or toxic hazardous wastes as a component of the waste stream.
<p>
The proposal does not include regulatory language, but rather includes a discussion of three options EPA is considering to promulgate.  The options provide a range of emission control methods, and varying degrees of overlap with other regulatory programs.  They range from relying on existing programs (e.g. RCRA LDR Phase III, Clean Air Act, etc.) for adequate environmental protection, to requiring specific mass removal equivalency to the Universal Treatment Standards (UTS) at the point of waste generation before it enters the impoundment.
<p>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> ERM Can Help </KBD></FONT>
<P>
Environmental Resources Management (ERM), Inc. can put our expertise  to work for you by assisting you in the following areas:
<p>
<ul>
<li>Assessing the impact to your facilities and developing comments for submission to EPA regarding this proposed rule.
<p>
<li>Evaluate impacts under each of the three management options EPA has proposed
to aid in your capital and management planning.
<p>
<li>Develop a pollution prevention program which may prevent LDR Phase IV and other pending RCRA regulations from affecting your facility.
<p>
</ul>
If you need assistance in any of these areas or other environmental challenges, call Rich Dulcey at (610) 524-3610 in Exton, PA.
<p>

<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> Key Features: </KBD></FONT>
<p>


<ul>
<li>Would affect Subtitle D and Clean Water Act impoundments.
<p>
<li>Affected facilities may be required to treat wastewater to remove underlying constituents before they enter impoundments.
<p>
<li>Three options presented with increasing complexity and control, comments are requested on the options.
<p>
<li>Preventing cross-media transfer to groundwater may require affected facilities to perform liner retrofitting.
<p>
<li>Would require quarterly sampling averaged to a yearly concentration for all hazardous constituents, which would be compared to the UTS to assess compliance.
<p>
<li>Sludges removed from the affected units would need to meet UTS even if they are not hazardous wastes.
<p>
<li>Air emissions would be regulated consistent with Subpart CC - i.e. >100 ppm VOC at point of generation would trigger applicability.
</ul>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
