<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H3> 
Chromium Plating MACT Requirements
</H3>

<I>Action:</I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> USEPA Promulgated Standard </FONT><BR>
<I>Date:</I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> Published January 25, 1995 </FONT><BR>
<I> For More Information Contact: </I><BR>
<FONT SIZE="-1"> Arbind Prasad<BR>
Exton, PA<BR>
(610) 524-3734 </FONT>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD>Introduction</KBD></FONT>
<P>

A "Maximum Achievable Control Technology Standard" was promulgated by the U.S. EPA on January 25, 1995.  All  chromium plating tanks are affected sources, including:
<p>
<ul>
<li>Hard Chromium Electroplating (1.3 to 760 microns)
<p>
<li>Decorative Chromium Electroplating 
(0.003 to 2.5 microns)
<p>
<li>Chromium Anodizing
<p>
</ul>
These sources must meet the emission limits specified in the standard and adhere to work practice standards.  Decorative Chromium platers must comply by January 1996, while hard chromium platers have until January 1997.  Have you determined whether your plating operation will comply?  Environmental Resources Management (ERM), Inc. has the staff available now to assist you in determining your status and meeting your obligations. 
<P>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD>How Can ERM Can Help?</KBD></FONT>
<P>
ERM has extensive experience in characterizing and evaluating chrome plating emissions.  We can put our expertise to work for you to help you demonstrate compliance with the new standard.
<p>
ERM has the capabilities to design and install a turnkey control system that meets the requirements of the standard.  Our expertise in related fields can insure that an air quality solution does not become a wastewater headache.  If you need assistance with air quality compliance, Title V, or other environmental challenges, either use the attached fax sheet or call Arbind Prasad at (610) 524-3735 in Exton, PA.
<p>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> Key Features: </KBD></FONT>
<p>
<ul>
<li>The standard applies different limits and control  requirements to  "Large" and  "Small" facilities based on their total potential ampere-hour per year capability.  Broader latitude is also built in for existing facilities.
<p>
<li>The standard contains test methods to demonstrate compliance with the numerical limits.
<p>
<li>The standard contains work practice standards in the form of inspection guidelines and inspection frequency requirements.
</ul>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
<IMG SRC="/gif/button_bar.gif" WIDTH=484 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ISMAP USEMAP="#buttonbar"></a>
</center>
