<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H3> 
 Pennsylvania's State Operating Permit Program 
</H3> 
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD>Introduction</KBD></FONT>
<P>

All facilities in Pennsylvania that did not submit 
a Title V permit application this past year must submit a minor source operating permit application either within 120 days from the time they receive notification (letter) from the Department of Environmental Protection (DEP)  or no later than 1 November 1996.  The State operating 
permit program application requires that facilities estimate emissions of regulated pollutants and complete detailed application forms which are available from the DEP.
<p>

<BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> ERM Can Help </KBD></FONT>
<P>

<ul>
<li>ERM staff can either prepare an emission inventory for your facility or review an existing inventory for completeness.
<p>
<li>ERM has prepared numerous operating permit applications for a wide variety of industries in Pennsylvania and across the nation.  We can help you assess your 
facility to formulate an approach that will lead to compliance with the DEP minor source operating permit program in a cost-effective and rapid manner. 
</ul>
<p>
Environmental Resources Management (ERM), Inc. has the capabilities to perform a complete project, or we can be involved selectively in those areas where you specifically need assistance.  If you need assistance with DEPUs minor source operating permit program or other environmental 
issues, either use the attached fax sheet or call Peter Charrington at ERM in Exton, Pennsylvania at (610) 524-3431 or Katie Klaber in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania at (412) 772-1022.

<p>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><KBD> Key Features: </KBD></FONT>
<p>

<ul>
<li> All facilities previously grandfathered from DEP permit programs must be included in the program.
<p>
<li> The permit application asks for substantial emissions related information and a review of existing operations to make certain the facility 
is in compliance with all applicable regulations.
</ul>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
<IMG SRC="/gif/button_bar.gif" WIDTH=484 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ISMAP USEMAP="#buttonbar"></a>
</center>
