<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<H3> 
UPDATE: Process Safety Management 
</H3>
<HR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
You may know Environmental Resources Management (ERM), Inc. from our air, engineering, remediation, wastewater, information management or environmental quality management (EQM) services.  There is more - an eight-year history of effective Process Safety Management (PSM) 
support to clients.
<p>
By May 26 of this year, hundreds of companies were required to perform a self-audit of their OSHA Process Safety Management program (29 CFR 1910.119), retrain process operators and complete 50% of required process hazards analyses (PHAs).
<p>
If a facility has more than a specified amount of a highly hazardous chemical in a process, it is covered by the standard.  The facility does not have to be a chemical plant to be covered by the standard.  For example, breweries, food, pharmaceutical, paint, ink, floor tiles and explosives manufacturers can all be covered by the standard.  ERM professionals are currently working with most types of industry on PSM issues.
<p>
ERM's environmental, health and safety specialists have assisted clients in managing PSM programs since the first state regulations were promulgated in New Jersey and Delaware. 
We offer cost-effective and timely PSM auditing services; audits usually involve a visit of two
to four days.
<p>
ERM provides comprehensive written management programs, PHAs, piping and instrumentation drawings (P&IDs) and all other PSM engineering and management services.  Many of you are now considering how the EPA Title V Risk Management Program (RMP) requirement may apply to your chemical processes.  ERM is already providing companies like yours with integrated process safety/risk management services.
<p>
ERM believes that Process Safety Management and Risk Management Planning may be the most important environmental, health and safety topics of the 1990s and we are prepared
to apply our PS/RM experiences to your specific requirements.  Use the attached fax sheet
or call Joe Baker at (610) 524-3500 to let us know how we can assist you or provide
additional information.
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<center>
<a href="/map/buttonbar.map">
