<a name="overview"></a><P>
<img src="barover.jpg"><br><table><tr><td colspan=2>
<font size=+1><b><i>What can A*I*M*S - Title V  do for your facility?</i></b></font size><BR>

With a focus on Title V air permit development and compliance management,
A*I*M*S-Title V will:<BR>
</td></tr><tr><td valign=top>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Create a unified air information database resource, capable of customized
querying and flexible reporting; and able to manage information on individual
source equipment, control devices, and emission points;
<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Calculate and compile air emissions estimates, organized by emission source
operating conditions for operational flexibility, what-if analyses, tracking
of actual and potential emissions, and emission limits;
<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Track regulatory applicable (as well as non-applicable) requirements and
the required compliance methods, such as monitoring, recordkeeping, testing,
monitoring, and workpractices;<BR>
</td><td valign=top>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Compile other air compliance resources, such as materials usage and composition;
non-air waste outputs; and compliance-related action item tracking and scheduling;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Track annual actual facility emissions for the Annual Emissions Statement,
and easily track modifications for potential regulatory applicability (e.g.,
New Source Review, MACT, etc.);<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Provide inputs for other regulatory reporting requirements, such as Toxic
Release Inventory (TRI) reports and emergency planning;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Allow self-assessment/auditing and tracking of compliance status with
applicable requirements;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Generate a &quot;Compliance Calendar&quot; for ongoing compliance schedules.<BR>
</td></tr></table>


<P>
<table cellpadding=10><tr><td colspan=2>

<a name="features"></a><center><a href="#top"><img src="top.jpg" border=0></a><br></center><img src="barfeature.jpg"><br>
<font size=+1><b><i>How does A*I*M*S-Title V work?</i></b></font size><BR>
<HR></td></tr><tr><td width=50% valign=top>
Air permitting-based design; a focus on Title V permitting; intuitive user
interfaces; and a minimal learning curve;<BR>
<BR>
Relational database in Microsoft Access 2.0, (a part of Microsoft Office,
suite), running in Windows 3.1/Windows 95; <BR>
<BR>
Microsoft Access&#174; is a premier desktop PC relational database environment; with spreadsheet-like
views of data; intuitive querying and reporting features; import/export,
connectivity with Excel, /Lotus, spreadsheets, other databases; <BR>
<BR>
LAN (Local Area Network) compatible;<BR>
</td><td valign=top>
Relational database structure compatible with client-server database software
such as Oracle,, Microsoft SQL Server, and Sybase, <BR>
<BR>
Un-compiled application for maximum facility flexibility and allowing future
modifications to suit evolving needs;<BR>
<BR>
Uses existing air emissions and source data available in electronic format,
e.g., Excel, spreadsheets;<BR>
<BR>
Readily customizable to meet the structure of individual state Title V programs,
and to be able to generate database reports that meet the format and content
of state Title V application forms.<BR>
<BR></td></tr></table>

<BR><a name="capabilities"></a><center><a href="#top"><img src="top.jpg" border=0></a><br></center><br><img src="barcap.jpg"><br><table cellpadding=5><tr><td colspan=2>
A*I*M*S-Title V's modular design allows you to selectively use its built-in
features to achieve your goals.  Focused on Title V permitting and compliance,
the modular design allow progressively expanded use to meet future needs.
 Current built-in capabilities include:<BR>
</td></tr><tr><td valign=top width=50%>
<h3>LIBRARY MODULE<hr></h3>

Resources to minimize repetitive tasks and help in data validation, such
as:<BR>
<br>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Applicable requirements lookup;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Over 600 regulated Chemicals and Properties, and chemical/physical properties;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Facility emission factor lookup;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Title V regulatory exempt/trivial/ insignificant activities lookup;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Facility contact and location lookups<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Materials definition and composition module, including purchased materials
MSDS and on-site blended materials management<BR>

<h3>AIR OBJECTS MODULES<hr></h3>
Defines Air Objects at the facility and their attributes related to air
permitting/ compliance.  Air Objects include the Facility, Emissions Sources,
Emission Units (Groups), Control Devices, and Emission Points.  Facility
details of owner/operator and Title V submittals; Control Device details
of type, operational parameters, control efficiency; Emission Unit definition
of grouped sources; and Emission Point stack and fugitive parameters.<h3>
EMISSION SOURCE MODULE<hr></h3>
Emission source information, including:
<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Title V permitting exemption status and rationale (if applicable);<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Type and operational information;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Unlimited &quot;Operating Conditions&quot; (scenarios), with individual
actual and potential hours of operation and     production parameters;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Materials Usage (hourly and annual) by source Operating Condition;<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Source-specific detail data for over 8 different source types, e.g., painting, storage tanks, combustion.

<h3> EMISSION STREAM MODULE<hr></h3>
Defines pollutant emission streams from each Emission Source through Control
Devices (if applicable) to Emission Points (point/fugitive).  Tracks multiple
exhaust configurations for each Emission Source, assigned by Operating Condition;
and Federal enforceability tracking for potential-to-emit.
<h3>
APPLICABLE REQUIREMENTS<br>
AND COMPLIANCE METHODS<hr></h3>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Applicable requirements and compliance methods for Facility; Emission
Unit; and Emissions Source (by Operating Condition);<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Applicable requirements by citation, description, type (e.g., emission
limit, operational limitation, other), pollutant, and compliance method
requirements;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Compliance status tracking and non-compliance action plans;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Compliance method by applicable requirement, including details of monitoring,
testing, recordkeeping, reporting and workpractice;
</td><td valign=top width=50%><h3>
EMISSIONS CALCULATIONS<hr></h3>
Flexible emissions estimation by Emission Source Operating Condition:<BR>
<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Actual and potential, hourly and annual emissions and basis;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Emission factor and basic mass balance calculations;<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Control efficiency by exhaust configuration; and enforceability for potential
emissions calculation;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Material use/balance calculations from usage and composition data, and
non-air waste emission module;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Incorporation of existing/new Excel, (or other) spreadsheets with emissions
calculations;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">What-if scenario evaluation;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Assist tools, including &quot;Copy Calculations&quot;; and &quot;List
Pollutants from Materials&quot; based on materials use and composition.<h3>
REPORTING MODULES<hr></h3>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Air Object information reports;<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Applicable requirements and self-assessment format reports;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Compliance method reports;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Facility emission inventory report;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">State Permit reports, providing a menu for State Title V application forms
<h3>
STATE-SPECIFIC MODULES<hr></h3>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Pennsylvania (complete);<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Jefferson County, KY; Oklahoma; New York<h3>
 FACILITY MODULES<hr></h3>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Multiple facility and sub-facility grouping and datafile management;<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Annual data archival;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Security and user privilege options.<h3>
 DESIGNED CAPABILITIES <hr></h3>
(Not currently implemented/in-progress)<BR>
<img src="globebut.jpg">Source production/operations tracking;<BR>

<img src="globebut.jpg">Compliance scheduling and reporting;Excess emissions/deviations reporting.</td></tr></table>



