<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Getting Personal
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="../images/personal.gif">
<P><FONT SIZE=+1><center>Welcome to Getting Personal -- the area in WomenSpace where we explore matters of the mind, body and heart for young women. </center><BR><BR>
<BR><BR></FONT>
<center><IMG SRC="../images/ruleyl.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>
<P><a href="03camp.html"><b>Women on the Internet</b></a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Careers in CyberSpace are certainly no longer the stronghold of men.  Courtney Macavinta interviewed one conqueror of the online world, Susanna Camp, a senior producer at Hotwired.  The first in a series, this feature story highlights Camp's unique perspective on working in CyberSpace.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>	
<center><IMG SRC="../images/ruleyl.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>

<P><a href="03fitness.html"><b>Fitness</b></a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>With Spring just around the corner, this issue of Getting Personal deals with some of the things we all think about right before its time to take off that winter coat -- to don T-Shirts, shorts and bathing suits.  Forget about "no pain no gain"- <B>no fun no fitness</B>, we say! WomenSpace's new personal trainer, will inspire you to start getting in shape for summer with <a href="03fitness.html">Advice from Anthony</a>. We've also got the <a href="topten.html">Top Ten</a> reasons to exercise from WomenSpace's own Sports Medicine Doc.

</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR></P> 
<center><IMG SRC="../images/ruleyl.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>
<a href="../bodyshock/03depress.html">Depression- How to Fight and Win</a><BR>
Special Feature From BodyShock!<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>If you've ever felt a bit down, you've probably experienced depression in some form or another. Occasional depression, or, "the blues" is natural for teenage girls.  But what happens when you can't ever seem to shake a feeling of sadness or helplessness? Cheryl Alkon takes a frank look at teenage depression and how to determine if you may need help to feel better.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>


