<TITLE>
WomenSpace: BodyShock!
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="../images/bodyshock.gif" BORDER=0>
<P>
<FONT SIZE =+1><center><BR>Welcome to the cool place for girls in WomenSpace.  <BR>In BodyShock!<TT><SUP>TM</SUP></TT>, we talk about all the things that matter to girls.   </center><BR><BR><BR><BR></P>

<center><IMG SRC="../images/rulepk.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>

<a href="angelspring.html">Angel and Bell</a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>If you didn't get to meet Angel and Bell in the last issue, <a href="angelspring.html">click here</a> to say hello. And now you order the BodyShock!<TT><SUP>TM</SUP></TT> Survival Kit which comes with Angel's booklet on how to make it through the BodyShock! years. <a href="../../bodyshock/bshockkit.html">Click here</a> to find out more about how to order.<BR></BLOCKQUOTE>

<center><IMG SRC="../images/rulepk.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>
<a href="03depress.html">Depression- How to Fight and Win</a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>If you've ever felt a bit down, you've probably experienced depression in some form or another. Occasional depression, or, "the blues" is natural for teenage girls.  But what happens when you can't ever seem to shake a feeling of sadness or helplessness? Cheryl Alkon takes a frank look at teenage depression and how to determine if you may need help to feel better.</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<center><IMG SRC="../images/rulepk.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>

<a href="getfit.html">Staying Fit</a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>Forget "no pain, no gain"-- we say no fun, no fitness! Here's some unique ways to stay in shape while having a great time.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<center><IMG SRC="../images/rulepk.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>

<a href="03embarr.html">Totally Embarrassing Tales!</a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>WomenSpace readers reveal their most embarrassing moments ... and they're not as uncommon as you might think!</P></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<center><IMG SRC="../images/rulepk.gif" BORDER=0></center><BR>

<a href="angelpower.html">With The Help of A Friend, You Can Handle It!</a><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE><P>Don't let an embarrassing moment get you down!  Afterall, we all go through 'em.  Take a look at a great story by <a href="jessica.html">Jessica</a> -- who saved her friend from a potentially embarassing moment.  And check out <a href="angelpower.html">Angel's advice</a> for dealing with embarrassing moments -- and the all around BodyShock! blues.</BLOCKQUOTE>
