<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Get Fit
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="../images/bodyshock.gif"><BR><BR>
<H1>Staying Fit </H1></center>
<B ><FONT SIZE=+1>Forget expensive, crowded gyms. To get in shape, all you may need is a pair of sneakers, a little free time, and some wide-open spaces</FONT>
<center><img src="../images/rulepk.gif"></center>
<BR>
<p>by Kym May</p></B>
<p>	<blockquote>
 First off, if you look good, you'll feel good. And while you should always love your body and accept the way you look, when you feel that you look good physically and you feel strong then you'll feel confident and happier. There are also physiological benefits from exercise (see below for a link to our Top Ten) .</p>
<p>There are different kinds of exercise-- including aerobic and anaerobic. Aerobic exercises involve the large muscle groups (your legs and arms) and increases your heart rate.  It's good for your heart, burns calories, and you'll lose excess fat. Anaerobic activities, in which you work hard in short spurts (such as weight training) build and strengthen your muscles. It's what gives you a firm, toned look and makes you stronger.</p>
<p>To get all the good benefits, you should try to exercise regularly, several times a week. When you do-- do something FUN!!!  You don't need to go to an expensive gym or hire a personal trainer to get in shape-- just grab a frisbee and a friend and head over to the nearest park.  Here are some suggestions of ways to exercise that are so much fun you'll forget that old adage, "no pain, no gain":</p></BLOCKQUOTE>
<UL>
<LI><B>Ice skating/ rollerblading--</B> Two of my all-time faves, I think that there's nothing like the feel of wind in your hair as you glide along.  And, it's a great way to meet cute, athletic boys!<BR>
<LI><B>Ultimate Frisbee--</B> If you can get a group of people together, this sport will keep you moving.  It's sort of a cross between soccer and football, but with a frisbee. And there's no referees- fouls and goals get called by a sort of honor system called 'Spirit of the Game.' Do a yahoo search for Ultimate Frisbee web sites for the rules and for information on local frisbee teams that you can join, or call the Ultimate Players' Association at 1-800-UPA-GETH (that stands for Get Horizontal- as when catching a low-to-the-ground frisbee). <BR>
<LI><B>Dancing--</B> Dance the night away at a club or party, and you'll burn off lots of spare calories! Or take a dancing class-- you can go wild with some exotic styles, like salsa, meringue, or even belly dancing!<BR>
<LI><B>Walking--</B> Do it fast, do it long, and it's one of the best (and cheapest) ways to get in shape.  It's even better for you than running or jogging, because it's non-jarring and non-impact, and better for your bones and joints.<BR>
<LI><B>Biking--</B> If you don't have a bike, check the yellow pages for rental shops in your area. Then hop on and take it for a spin around the neighborhood!  Tone those legs! (Just be careful on the open road, and wear a helmet!)<BR>
<LI><B>Weights--</B> Get a set of hand weights and a video.  Or if you don't want to make the investment, give it a go with a couple of 1 or 2 pound bags of rice or beans (just be careful you don't puncture them and fling grains around the house).<BR>
</UL>
<center><B>Don't forget-- "Train, don't strain."  Work hard, but don't overdo it!</center></B>

<center><img src="../images/rulepk.gif"></center><BR>
<P>To learn more about fitness, tune into <a href="../gettingpersonal/03fitness.html">Advice from Anthony</a>, WomenSpace's personal trainer! And don't forget to check out the list of the <a href="../gettingpersonal/topten.html">Top Ten</a> reasons to exercise from WomenSpace's Sports Medicine Doc!</P>
<center><img src="../images/rulepk.gif"></center><BR>
