<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Best Friends
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="../images/bodyshock.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+1><center>Sometimes its hard to know who your true blue friends are -- until the going gets tough!  But the best way to make sure that your friends look out for you is to always look out for them!  In this great story written by a frequent WomenSpace surfer, Jessica, a grrl finds out about the true loyalty of her friend.</center>
</FONT><BR>
<center><img src="../images/rulepk.gif"></center>
<BR><BR>
<b>by Jessica Wilber</b>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Once, at the beginning of seventh grade, my friend Rachel and I had a free hour.  We were outside on the playground, when all of a sudden I noticed that she had blood on the back of her pants!</P>
<P>"Rachel!" I hissed</P>
<P>"What?!" she asked me.</P>
<P>"You have blood on the back of your pants!" I whispered  to her.</P>
<P>So, she immediately ran inside to the bathroom.</P>
<P>Later that day, she said something to me that really made me feel good.</P>
<P>"Thanks -- I'll look out for you too."</P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>This story was submitted by Jessica Wilber -- who has a great web site of her own.  Check it out by <a href="http://pages.prodigy.com/WI/jessica/heyworldindex.html">clicking here</a>.</P><BR>



<center><img src="../images/rulepk.gif"></center><BR>
<center>
<a href="../index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/wstool.gif" BORDER=0></a><BR>
