<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Shaving
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1>

<P>
Along with all the other not-so-subtle changes that happen to your body during puberty, one of them is the fact that your body begins to produce hair in various places -- in your armpits, in the triangle over your pubic bone --and you probably already have hair on your legs that has been there since you were small. <P>
<P>
Lots of girls begin to think about shaving at some point along the way to adulthood. But shaving can turn into quite a task once you've begun. In fact, many women choose not to shave at all!  Quite honestly, there is no real medical reason to shave -- the decision to do it is usually a cultural or social one. <P>
<P>
If it's something you've been considering, it's probably worth taking a moment to learn more about it, to speak with your mom or dad or another adult about it, and to weigh just how important it is to you. 
<P>If you've done all this and you've decided that shaving is something you want to do, take a look below at some pointers from the experts!  </FONT><P>


<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="ladypers.gif"><strong>From the Experts</strong>:<BR>Get 6 great <a href="asrztips.html"><b>Insider Tips</b></a> from the makers of Lady Personna Plus! ... See why the experts believe that <a href="wetshaving.html"><B>Wet Shaving</B></a> is the absolute best! ... And take a look at advice about shaving from fashion models in <a href="models.html"><B>Eight Models' Tips for Pretty Legs.</B></a>.<P><P>
<strong>Thia's Thoughts On ... </strong><BR>
Which shaving accessory is the best -- <a href="thiarating.html"><b>Soap, Foam or Gel</b></a>?  Thia tried them all out -- and here are her ratings!<P>
<P>
<strong>Some General Pointers</strong><BR>
Take a look at some <a href="generalpointers.html"><b>general advice</b></a> on what to shave-- and what not to shave! Once you've figured all this out, check out some safety tips on where to shave</b>.

</FONT>
