<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Pimples
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">
<BR>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif" BORDER=0>
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<CENTER>A special feature story ...<BR>My Pimple or My Dimple?
Which One Will They Notice?</CENTER><BR><BR>
<P>

Every day when I wake up and I never know what to expect. There is so much going on with my body, I feel like I'm on a roller coaster ... !! <P>
<P>
One day ... I got out of bed, stumbled to the bathroom, reached for my toothbrush, and THEN, suddenly, right before my eyes, I saw it!!  Right there, right smack dab in the middle of my cute little dimple was a <em> red, bulging, awful PIMPLE!</em><P>
<A NAME="1"><P>
I couldn't believe it, my very first pimple ever.   I thought I could make it all the way through high school without one. But NOOOO! It had to happen.  And it had to happen on that day -- the day when I had so much going on!! We're talkin' <a href="stress.html"><b>Stress-- with a capital S!</b></a>
<P>

At 9:00 am, I had a History report that I had to present in front of the class.  At 3:00 pm, I had try outs for chorus and then, later that night, I had my first date ever with Michael -- the boy of my dreams!! <P>  
<A NAME="2"><P>
What was I to do!!  <a href="pimplesolutions.html"><b>Scrub it? Pop it? Hide it?</b></a><P>
<P>

While trying to decide between my options, I looked in the mirror and, just for the heck of it, I pretended I had just ran into Michael:  I gave myself my most <em>dazzling</em> smile and said "Hi, Michael -- how are you?" <P>
<P>
It was amazing! When I smiled, the pimple in my dimple almost totally disappeared!!  The wider I smiled, the less you could see it. I had found my solution!!<P>
<P>
I got dressed and headed off to school. When I arrived, I put on a my best smile and wore it for the rest of the day ...<P>

When I gave my History report in front of the class, the teacher gave me a great grade for being so "enthusiastic." When I tried out for the chorus, I got a spot right away because they liked how "happily" I sang. And later that night, on my date with Michael, he told me that he loved my smile because I had beautiful <em>dimples</em>!  Can you believe it?<P>
<P>
Since that day, I haven't worried about pimples. Whenever I get them, I don't hide them, I just smile.  Afterall, they can't possibly notice my pimples when they see my great smile and dimples! <P></FONT>

<HR>
