<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Angel
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>

<a href="bodshk.html">Back to BodyShock Main Page</a> | <a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="personal.html">Getting Personal</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a>
<BR><a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<P><CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<img src="images/body.gif" BORDER=0>
<BR>She's here!  She's here! <BR><BR><BR>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="images/angel3.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR><P>Hi, I'm Angel!  <BR>And this is my best friend, Bell!</P>
<P>Listen up, girls!  I've got some things <BR>to tell you about this whole "growing up" thing. <BR> Your health teacher, your mom, your <BR>older sister might call it "puberty" -- <BR>but I call it <BR>BodyShock!!<BR><BR>'Cause with all the crazy, random things that happen <BR>to your body  --  a perfectly calm, cool girl <BR>could go totally nuts trying to figure it all out!</P>
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/juggle.gif" BORDER=0>You know what I mean ... <BR>you're cruising through life with everything<BR> under control -- and then, all of a sudden, <BR> somebody throws in stuff like <BR>acne, shaving, bras ... and this <BR>whole "period" business!<BR><BR>But trying to juggle them <BR>with all your other stuff can be <BR>a bit too much!<BR><BR></P>
<P>I remember the day somebody finally <BR>clued me in on what it meant to "start my period!"  
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="images/what.gif" BORDER=0>
<P>I was totally like ...<BR><BR>"I'm going to do WHAT?  <BR>From WHERE? <BR>For HOW long?!!"<BR></P>
<P>And ...  as if finding out about all this<BR> wasn't bad enough, I had girls like <BR>Miss Information <BR> 
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="images/facts.gif" BORDER=0>telling me all kinds of crazy myths<BR> about starting my period ... <BR>all of which turned out to be totally false! </P>
<P>I had had enough!  So I set out on a mission to find out the facts myself!  And I'm happy to report that I've compiled them into my handy-dandy booklet called <b>Ten Rules To Survive BodyShock!</b> </P>
 </CENTER>
<P>It's a totally cool guide to separating the truth from the myths about starting your period and growing up. <a href="orderform.html">Just click here to find out how to get it!</a>
<BR><BR><BR>
</FONT>
