<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Who Purchases...
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+1><BR><BR>
Who will purchase ...<BR><BR>
<P>
If you know that you will be the primary person responsible for purchasing the the birth control method that you
and your partner choose, it is important to look into the costs associated
with using each one.<P>

For instance, birth control pills can cost as little as a few dollars each month if you purchase them at a student health public clinic -- or they can cost as much as $20 or $30 per month at a retail drug store.  You'll also need to get a prescription for birth control pills which will require a visit to your health care provider.  Again, this cost may vary depending on where you go for an examination. <P>
Other methods such as condoms do not require you to get an examination from your health care provider but the cost of using them can add up.  Depending on where you purchase them, you can expect to pay around $5.00 for a package of six condoms.  So, from this, you can determine how much you will spend on condoms each time you have sexual intercourse. <P>
The important thing to realize is that having "safe and protected sex" isn't always "cheap".  Therefore, before making the decision to have sexual intercourse -- take just a moment to determine if your budget will always allow you to have access to the birth control method you choose. <P>

FYI -- Though the cost of birth control may seem expensive to you at times, it is certainly safer and less expensive than an unwanted pregnancy.  So take care of yourself by looking into all the birth control methods available.<P>
</FONT>
