<FONT SIZE=+1><BR><BR>
Who will purchase ...<BR><BR>
<P>
Sharing in the cost of the birth control method is a fantastic way for the
both of you to take equal responsibility for your decision to become
sexually active.  As you explore the various birth control methods
available to you and your partner, take a look at the costs associated with
using each of them -- and speak with your partner about how much you think each of you can expect to spend. <P>
For instance, birth control pills can cost as little as a few dollars each month if you purchase them at a student health public clinic -- or they can cost as much as $20 or $30 per month at a retail drug store.  You'll also need to get a prescription for birth control pills which will require a visit to your health care provider.  Again, this cost may vary depending on where you go for an examination. <P>
