<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Shaving
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1><BR><BR>
<CENTER>Six Great Insider Tips<BR><BR><BR></CENTER>
<P>
<BR><BR><BR>
<HR><CENTER>Sponsored by <BR><img src ="ladypers.gif"><BR>Twin Blade Disposable Razors</CENTER>
<HR>

1.  Don't shave as soon as you get up in the morning.  Everyone's skin is a little puffy first thing.  Wait for at least half an hour and you will get a better shave. <P>
2.  Shower or bathe before you shave.  Soak legs / underarms in a luxurious warm bath or shower for two to three minutes.   Use lots of soap and water.  That softens and expands the hairs making them easier to remove.<P>
3.  Use soap or a shaving preparation like moisturised cream or gel.  Apply liberally.  Smooth the gel upwards from the ankles to help the hairs stand up ready for shaving.<P>
4.  Use a sharp blade.  Make sure you change it often enough (for most women this is afer one or two sessions) since a blunt blade will pull and irritate the skin.  Never wipe the blade with a cloth or towel as this will damage the blade.  Simply shake and leave to dry.<P>
5.  Using a light touch, shave with, and then against the growth using short strokes.  Rinse the razor frequently.  Check with your fingers to be sure you have the smooth close feeling. <P>
6.  After shaving, many women finish with a moisturizing lotion for a silky smooth feeling. <P>
</FONT>
