<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Shaving
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<P>
Why shave with a razor instead of shaving with an electric razor, waxing or using hair removal chemicals??  Because the experts say ...<BR><P>
<b>Wet Shaving</b> is truly the modern way; clean, fresh and hygienic.  You can shave as part of the daily routine of washing in bath or shower.  Best of all, it leaves your skin smooth and silky to the touch. <P>
An added plus is the removal of old, dry dead skin cells which leaves your skin feeling fresh and smooth.  <P>
Wet shaving is gaining in popularity worldwide mainly because beauty therapists and research by dermatologists indicate that wet shaving is not only quicker, but is more effective, more hygienic and less harmful to your skin in the long term.
<P>
Some people believe that wet shaving makes hair grow back more quickly when compared to other methods.  There is no evidence to support this.
<P>
<HR>
