<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Shaving
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<CENTER>What to shave, <BR>what not to shave <BR>and where! ... <BR>some general pointers.<BR><BR><BR><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<A NAME="1"><center><b>What to Shave</b></center><BR>
The areas that women choose to shave vary pretty widely -- some women only shave their armpits and not their legs, others only shave their calves and not their thighs, some women shave the outer areas of their pubic hair. <P>
<P>
If you have very fine or light-colored hair on your legs, you may find no reason to shave them at all.  Many <em>moms</em> prefer that their daughters only shave their calves in the beginning. Sometimes, women decide to shave more extensively in the summer when they wear bathing suits, shorts and tank tops. <P>
<P>
What to shave is a very personal decision -- there is no right or wrong way. But it may be best to choose a small area first to get an idea of just how much work -- and maintenance -- is involved before deciding to shave everything!!<P>
<P>
<A NAME="2"><center><B>What Not to Shave</B></center><BR>
<strong>Don't shave your mustache</strong>:  Although you may find that the hair above your
lip may become darker as you go through puberty, we don't recommend shaving it. Often, shaving this hair can result in it becoming darker and coarser when it grows back. Other solutions to this "mustache" problem are to wax it or to bleach it. Both of these methods can be purchased in the drug store -- or you can go to a salon to have it done. Waxing can be a little painful but it usually takes care of the mustache for as long as four weeks. <P>

<strong>Don't shave your eyebrows</strong>: Most razors aren't small enough to be as precise as you need for your eyebrows -- not to mention that it probably isn't a good idea to put something as sharp as razor near your eyes. If you want to shape your eyebrows, you have a couple of options -- plucking them or waxing them. Both of these methods can be a little painful so you may want to skip them completely. Many fashion magazines -- and lots of adult women -- believe that natural eyebrows are the most attractive.
<P>

<A NAME="3"><center><b>Where To Shave</b></center><BR>
One shaving decision to make is whether to do it in the shower or in the tub. Shaving in the shower takes good balance -- and some extra care so that you don't slip. Some women place one foot on the side of the tub and bend down to shave.  Just make sure that your feet are firmly planted in an area that isn't soapy or slippery.<P>
<P>
Shaving in the tub requires less balance -- but make sure that your hands are not soapy so that you can hold the razor securely. Some women choose to shave separately from bathing -- by sitting on the side of the tub. This can give you more stability.<P>

</FONT>
<center><a href="shaving.html"><em>More Info On Shaving ...</em></a>
