<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">

<BR><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=+1>
<CENTER>Wrong!</CENTER>
<BR><BR><BR><BR>
Though it is true that when you have your period you are shedding the lining in your uterus which contains the egg that your ovaries released that month, it does not guarantee you that the egg can't be fertilized. Therefore, it isn't surprising that there are a significant number of women who do get pregnant as a result of having unprotected sex while they have their periods. </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#1">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER><P>

