<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">

<FONT SIZE=+1>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>Wrong again!</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<P>If you been having sex with your boyfriend for a while without using any birth control and you haven't gotten pregnant-- it probably just means you're very lucky. There is some chance that you have been having sex during the times of the month in which your ovaries have not produced an egg. But this is certainly not something with which you will want to roll the dice.  If you do not want to get pregnant, check into some of the methods of birth control available to you within our Birth Control Questionnaire. 
</P>

<P>Though the likelihood of you (or your boyfriend) being sterile is pretty slim, a trip to your gynecologist or health care provider can help you determine if you are, in fact, unable to become pregnant. </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#4">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER><P>

