<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>Forget It!</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<P>This one is just NOT true. There are lots of women who've had this exact scenario happen. Generally speaking, if you have had your first period -- then your ovaries are producing an egg each and every month. This egg slowly moves from your ovaries, to your fallopian tubes, to your uterus -- where it sits and waits to be fertilized. This process will happen regardless of whether you're having sex or not. So if during this time you have sex for the first time, you are very likely to fertilize that egg -- in other words, get pregnant!!</P>

<P>(PS -- There have been studies which have shown that some young women who have had sex or who have been raped before they had their first period became pregnant. Though details on this subject are sketchy -- it is better to go on the wisdom that you can, indeed, get pregnant the first time you have sex.) </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#6">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER><P>
<BR><BR>
