<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>Get a clue!</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<P>This method of birth control is called the "withdrawal" method and it means that the guy pulls his penis out of your vagina before he ejaculates (has an orgasm). Though many people consider this to be a valid form of birth control, it is simply untrue to say that you "can't" get pregnant when you use this method. In fact, the failure rate with this method can be quite high. </P>

<P>The reason for this is twofold: (1) Guys often have a small amount of "pre-ejaculation" fluid way before they have the real ejaculation -- both of which contain sperm. (2) Many guys aren't very good at controlling the timing with the withdrawal method. It is often difficult for them to know exactly when to "pull out" and, as a result, they may "pull out" too late. The result could be that some sperm is deposited into your vagina. </FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#7">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER<P>
<BR><BR>
