<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">

<FONT SIZE=+1>
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>Wrongo!</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
Many gynecologists recommend that you take a full cycle of birth control pills before you rely on them as your primary method of birth control. A "full cycle" means that you take a complete pack of the pills (which is an entire month) and then have your next period. Only after that point will your body have had time to adjust to the effects of the hormones in the Pills.</FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#8">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER><P>

