<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Miss Conceptions
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="DEA7D4">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">

<FONT SIZE=+1><BR><BR>
<CENTER>Wishful thinking!</CENTER>
<BR><BR>

<P>This myth is probably a result of someone not understanding women's anatomy too well!! When you have sex, the guy deposits sperm into your vagina. From there, the sperm swim up through your cervix and into your uterus. These parts of your body (your vagina, your cervix, your uterus) are in no way connected to your urinary tract or your gastro-intestinal tract. Thus, using the bathroom after having sex really won't do anything to "kill the sperm."</P>

<P>One addtional theory on this myth might be that when you sit down to use the bathroom, some of the ejaculation fluid which contains sperm may run out. Though it may be true that the sheer force of gravity will cause some of the fluid to come out, there are still millions of sperm that could still be inside your vagina.
</FONT>
<P>
<CENTER><a href="missconceptions.html#9">What Will She Think Of Next!</a></CENTER><P>

