<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Pimples
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1><BR><BR>
<CENTER>Stress -- With A Capital "S"!</CENTER><BR><BR>
<P>

Although doctors don't have a good explanation about why stress cause pimples -- one thing is for sure --  alot of young women say that when they're under alot of stress or anxiety, they are more likely to get them.

But stress isn't the main cause of pimples -- the amount of oil your skin produces is usually the primary culprit!  When your skin produces lots of oil, your pores can become clogged.  So try to have a daily routine of cleaning your face, neck and chest to remove excess oils and dead skin.  
<P>
</FONT>
<a href="pimple.html#1"><b>Back to the story ...</b></a>
