<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Pimples
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="F7B68B">
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">

<FONT SIZE =+1><CENTER>What should she do?<BR>
Scrub It? Pop It? Hide It?</CENTER><BR><BR>
<P>
Other than washing and cleaning your face, your best option for pimples is to leave them alone. Popping them can cause your skin to scar. It can also cause the pimple to become even redder and maybe even hang around alot longer. <P>

<P>If you notice that the pimple has a "white head" on it, it means that the pore has produced an excess of something called "sebum" (see-bum).  This sebum can clog the pore and lead to an infection -- which means that a there is pus underneath the skin. 
<P>
Sometimes washing a "white head" with a washcloth or a lightly abrasive scrub can help by releasing the sebum and pus.  But don't scrub too hard -- just enough to gently wash away the dead skin.<P>

<P>As far as hiding it, you're best bet may be an acne medication that comes in a "flesh tone."  Using a lot of make-up or cosmetic powder might hide it, but it certainly won't help heal it.  It's better to let it "breath" than cover it with too much make-up.<P>
</FONT>
<a href="pimple.html#2"><b>Back to the story ...</b></a>
