WomenSpace: Shaving
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="9FC3E4">

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="daisystem2.gif">
<FONT SIZE =+1><CENTER>Thia's Thoughts On ...<BR>
Soap, Foam or Gel?? Which is best?</CENTER><BR><BR><BR>
<P>
<em>Thia says... </em>The sacred rule of shaving is never, never dry shave!  Always lube up or you're in for a burn girl!  So here's the low down on what you can lube up with -- and which one I think is the best!<P>

<blockquote><strong>SOAP</strong> -- The good news about soap is that it's almost always available no matter where you are.  But the negative is that it can be sooo drying. (Can I get a Diet Coke here?)  You know you have to lather up so the razor will glide across your leg -- but there are alternatives to plain old body soap. <P>

<strong>SHAVING CREAM</strong> -- No doubt you've seen your dad, your brother or some macho hunk on TV with a white foamy face just before shaving -- and trusty shaving cream is their answer for a smooth shave.  But beware the smell and that bulky can.  While the Aloe scent is tolerable, you can do better girl!<P>
<strong>SHAVING GEL</strong> Now, here's where it's at!  The name <em>gel</em> says it all.  It goes on easily, out of the fem, slender can and it smells divine!  Skintemate is its name -- and a smooth shave is its super-crucial claim!  And smooth it is.  Check it out and don't shave again with out it!</blockquote><P>
