<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Reality
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<A NAME="7"><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="images/pers.gif"><BR><BR>
What's The Deal With <B>Reality</B> --<BR> The Female Condom?<BR><BR>Even more info ....<BR><BR></CENTER>
<P><BR><BR>
<b>How Does It Work?</b></FONT><BR>
Reality is a soft, lubricated plastic sheath that lines the vagina.  It fits like a second skin, adhering to the vaginal wall, and also protects the outside of the vagina.  It has a soft, flexible ring at each end.  The ring inside the closed end helps you to put the female condoms inside the vagina, and helps hold it in place.  The other ring, which forms the open end of the sheath, stays outside the vagina, and partly covers the lop area.</P>
<P>For the best effectiveness, use a Reality condom with every sex act, and use a new one every time you have sex.  Like all condoms (and seat belts, too) they only work when you use them!  It's also a good idea to use additional lubricant at first.  Put a few drops in the opening of the condom and on the penis.  The additional lubricant diminishes friction and will stop any noises you may hear.  If you wish, you can use spermicide with it too, by putting it inside the vagina before you insert the Reality female condom.</P>
<P>It really helps if you practice inserting Reality before you plan to use it with your partner during sex.  This way, you'll better understand how it works and what feels most comfortable for you before you actually need it!</P>
<CENTER><a href="reality.html#2">Back to Reality -- How Does It Feel?</a>
</CENTER>
<A NAME="2"><BR><BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1><b>What Do Other People Say About Reality?</b></FONT><BR><BR>
<em>Perception:</em><BR><BR>
"The first time my partner and I used the female condom, we laughed." - Estelle N., Graduate Student/Artist<BR><BR>
"I thought it was rather weird at first, to tell you the truth." -- Donna H., Nurses Assistant<BR><BR>
<em>Reality:</em><BR><BR>
"But after I used it a couple of times, it was 1-2-3 ... no problem." -- Debbie S., Hospital Employee<BR><BR>
"Once I got over the way it looks, I was comfortable.  It's the contraceptive for me." -- Donna H., Nurses Assistant <BR><BR></P>
<CENTER><a href="reality.html#3">Back to Reality -- You're In Control!</a></CENTER>
<A NAME="3"><BR><BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1>
<b>How Does It Protect Me?</b></FONT><BR>
The only 100% effective protection comes from abstinence.  No barrier method is 100% effective.  However, if Reality is used properly with every act of intercourse, it will provide protection against unintended pregnancy and will reduce the risk of sexually transmitted diseases.  The "typical" use failure rate using Reality in one six month study measuring contraception was 12%.  These women used Reality only sometimes or used it incorrectly.  When Reality was used properly every time, the failure rate was 3%.  Estimates of yearly failure rates are 19-25% for typical use and 5% for perfect use.</P>
<CENTER><a href="reality.html#4">Back to Reality -- Is It Weird?</a></CENTER>

<A NAME="4"><BR><BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1>
<b>How Do I Order Reality Through The Women's Pharmacy?</b></FONT><BR>
One of the biggest complaints we've heard from women about shopping in the retail drug store is the lack of privacy many feel when purchasing items like condoms, sanitary protection, pregnancy tests, etc.  The Women's Pharmacy enables you to shop for these items and more -- and have them delivered directly to your home.  <BR><BR>
