<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Anorexia and Bulimia
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
Category 1<BR>Anorexia Nervosa and Bulimia<BR>General Warning Signs<BR><BR><BR>
<P>If you can answer "yes" to two or more of the statements in Category 1, it certainly doesn't mean you have anorexia or bulimia -- but it might mean that you have an unhealthy or unrealistic view of yourself -- which is a classic symptom of women who do suffer from anorexia and bulimia. </FONT></CENTER></P>
<P>
A lot of young women go through times when they feel physically unattractive -- and even feel a little "out of control." But so much of these feelings are brought on as a result of unrealistic expectations we put on ourselves  -- like a need to be skinnier even when everyone else around us tells us that we're already thin enough!  </P>
<P>
For lots of young women and girls, it seems like weight is the only thing we can control in order to feel better about ourselves.  So many young women strive for perfection in everything -- and losing weight is just one way of feeling like we're doing this. </P>
<P>
Even though it's easier said than done ... it's extremely important to try and identify ourselves with things other than our weight.  For instance, ask yourself what you consider to be the best things about you ... </P>
<P>If your answer is something like "my hair, my legs, my chest" ... your focus may be too much on your physical self.  Just think about all the fantastic things about you that aren't purely physical -- the fact that you aced that math exam, the fact that you are an excellent soccer player or the fact that you have a great singing voice ... the list goes on and on! </P>
<P>When it comes right down to it -- your talents are the coolest, most interesting things about you! </P>
<HR>
<center><a href="eatdis.html#2">Go back for Category 2</a></center><BR>
<HR>
<center><a href="personal.html">Back to <BR>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0></a><BR><BR>
