<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Anorexia and Bulimia
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
Category 2<BR>Anorexia Nervosa<BR>Specific Warning Signs<BR><BR><BR>
<P>A "yes" to two or more of the statements in Category 2 means that you definitely should take a closer look at your health -- and preferably with a health care provider who can determine if these signs are cause for concern. </P></FONT></CENTER>
<P>Without question, these are classic symptoms of a person suffering from anorexia nervosa.  This eating disorder is one in which a person attempts to lose weight by decreasing the amount of food she eats -- and some quit eating altogether. </P>
<P>But when your body doesn't get the necessary nutrients it needs, it begins to shut down.  One of the main things affected is your menstrual cycle.  When your total body fat percentage falls below a certain level, your body is unable to produce the hormones that control having a period.</P>
<P>
Though it may sound great to stop having your period, it's really very dangerous when it happens as a result of not taking in enough calories.  Your body needs a certain level of calories everyday.  For a young woman, this may mean 1000 to 2000 calories each and every day to give your body the energy it needs.  When your body is deprived of this, you can feel tired, dizzy or worse!</P>
<HR>
<center><a href="eatdis.html#3">Go back for Category 3</a><BR></center>
