<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Anorexia and Bulimia
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<CENTER>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
Category 3<BR>Anorexia Nervosa<BR>Specific Alert Signs<BR><BR><BR>
If you can answer "yes" to two or more of the specific physical signs in Category 3 -- particularly if you also answered "yes" to statements in Category 2 -- you should see a health care provider to discuss your health.</FONT></CENTER></P>
<P>Category 3 lists symptoms of exactly what begins to happen to your body when it's not getting enough of the nutrients it needs.  Your skin, nails and hair are easily affected by a poor diet.  When you attempt an extreme diet or stop eating all together, you run the risk of truly hurting your body -- rather than helping it. </P>

