<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Pantyhose
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<P><CENTER>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1><BR>Question:  I like to wear tight stockings -- with a built-in support panty.  What are the pros and cons?<BR><BR></P>
<BR><BR>
<P><B>The benefits of wearing sturdy, tight stockings has been a secret <BR>of waitresses for a long time ... </FONT></P></CENTER></B>
<P>Lots of women who work in jobs that force them to stand on their feet for most of the day wear support-type stockings.  The benefit lies in the fact that the even pressure from the hose helps with the blood circulation in the legs.  Not only does is help by decreasing achey leg pain at the end of the day -- it also helps decrease the likelihood of getting varicose veins.</P>
<P>
<UL>(Varicose Veins -  ("vair-ah-kose") a condition in which poor circulation in the veins cause the vein to expand and protrude.  This condition can be genetic; however, special circumstances like excess pressure in the legs can force the condition to occur.)<BR></UL></P>
<FONT SIZE=+1><CENTER>
<P><B>Many young women find out the hard way <BR>what the problems are with wearing too tight stockings ...</FONT></P></B></CENTER>
<P>When stockings are too tight -- there is a good chance that your groin and pubic areas are not getting enough air.  This can result in the perfect environment for the micro-organisms that cause yeast infections to multiply!  Lots of young women who suffer from frequent yeast infections find that wearing looser pantyhose and wearing pantyhose less often can help decrease the number of yeast infection episodes they experience.</P>
</FONT>
<center><a href="hosehealth.html">Back to the Questionnaire</a></center>
