<HEAD>
<TITLE>
WomenSpace: Pantyhose
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center><IMG SRC="images/wssmall.gif" BORDER=0><BR><HR>
<a href="personal.html">Back to Getting Personal Main Page</a> <BR><a href="index.html">WomenSpace</a> | <a href="bodshk.html">BodyShock</a> | <a href="yogirls.html">Yo! Girls</a> | <a href="grrlstore.html">The Grrl Store</a> | 
<a href="extra.html">Extra! Extra!</a> | <a href="hotlinx.html">Hot Linx</a><BR>
<a href="../twp/pharmacy.html">The Women's Pharmacy</a></center>
<HR>
<FONT SIZE =+1>
<P><CENTER>
<img src="images/pers100.gif" BORDER=0><BR><BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=+1><BR>Question:  I like the hose with reinforced heels and toes.  Are there any benefits or problems with these?<BR><BR></P>
<BR><BR>
<P><B>The benefits are obvious...</B></FONT></CENTER></P>
<P>Although we haven't done an "official" study on this one, it's a pretty safe bet that the majority of runs in hose happen around the toes and heels.  Afterall, this is where the most friction happens.  So the best "health" benefit of reinforced toes might actually be for your wallet!  There is also some additional benefits to this due to the fact that the reinforced areas decrease any friction between your skin and your shoes -- protecting your heels and toes from blisters!
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<P><CENTER><B>The problems are not so obvious ...</B></CENTER></FONT></P>
<P>Because hose with reinforced heels and toes decrease friction between your skin and your shoes, you might not realize that your shoes don't fit properly.  Studies have shown that lots of women routinely buy shoes that are too small for them -- and the results can be painful!  Therefore, when shopping for shoes, don't be misled by wearing pantyhose that might make the shoes just "seem" to fit.  Also, make sure that your hose with reinforced heels and toes allow enough circulation -- both for blood and for air!  Too tight hose on your feet can play a role in achey, tired feet -- and can provide the perfect hot, moist environment for fungi to make a new home!
</P>
</FONT>
