<h3><i>Asians in Norway</i></h3>

<p><tt>Mon Oct 16 23:27 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>Dear Stormfront, I am a twenty-seven year old male in Northern 
Norway, married to a beautiful wife, Katia, and father of a 
beautiful daughter, Save.

<p>Please forgive my grammer. I have 
had very little contact with any "non-white" races, having
spent my life in Norway. But here in Velijord, our nearest neighbors
are Filipinos, or asians. I was a white supremacist when I was
younger boy, but I have changed that slightly. I do not know if
I support my previous views anylonger. Our neighbors are good 
people, and have helped us from time to time. I admit that I was
at first, bothered by them. Or perhaps, just fearful. But that 
turned out to be just a presumption that was unfounded. 

<p>I was
convinced to visit the United States, San Francisco to be exact,
to see if what television showed us was true. There were a great
number of Asians and whites in San Francisco, and I was surprised
to see such a mixture, but not surpised to see that they worked
so well together. In fact, one of my younger ideals when I was a 
skinhead was to somehow bring up a fourth reich with the Aryans 
of Europe, beginning in Germany, and to once again align 
this supremacist movement with the Japanese, who were ironically
better friends and allies to Adolf Hitler than the Italians were.
They reflected loyalty, honestly, and dogmatism, almost aryan in
their zeal. But anyway, in San Francisco, I was treated very well
by the Asians and especially my friends family. 

<p>Perhaps the only 
bad experience I had there was when we went a place called Oakland
and went to a mall. A group of black men approached us and asked
us to give them some money. My friend began to take out his
wallet when one of them suddenly struck him in the face. I was
suddenly angery and kicked the black man in the groin with my boots
(which I still retained from my skinhead days in Oslow). The others
came at me and my friend then, and we fought them off amazingly.
He apologized to me afterward for what had happened, and I 
could not understand why. They had attacked us, not the other
way around. We returned back to Norway, both of us a little
bruised from our encounter. I have realized that Asians are a
good people, and that I do not mind them as neighbors and friends.
But I am wondering now about how I would feel if black people
would move in to my country, and if they would show the same 
kindness. I was fearful of my daughter, Save, playing with my 
friend's daughter because I was still very prejudiced. But I have
found that my fears are not founded. They are now very good friends.
I still support white pride. I favor co-existence with Asians. But
I question whether or not blacks will be the same way. Please
understand that I am not a racist, but that I am trying to understand.   

<p><b>Heindrick Siglufijordur</b>
<br>Velijord-Bronnoysund, Norway


