<h3><i>The Zundelsite is up and running!</i></h3>

<p><tt>Sun Aug 27 20:43 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>This is to thank Stormfront for putting up the URL for Zundelsite. For convenience's sake, I am listing it again.  It is <a TARGET="_top" href="http://www.webcom.com/~ezundel/english/">http://www.webcom.com/~ezundel/english/</a>.  We are asking other individuals or groups involved in this movement to help us advertise it and use it to the fullest, because, as we all know, ZOG will try to shut it down.  By the way, we should use the term ZOG as much as possible, because it is an identifier and helps condense and summarize what this is all about.

<p>Keep up the good work, Don.

<p><b>Karin</b>
<br>San Diego, CA
<br><a href="mailto: "></a>

<hr>    

<h3><i>White Culture?</i></h3>

<p><tt>Sat Aug 26 15:54 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>I support your right to say what you like, but I question the logic
in some of your motives.  You say you celebrate white culture, and most
essayists here seem to be of the opinion that this white culture could
be destroyed by interracial breeding.  However: What do you consider
to be white culture?

<p>Whites in both the US and canada consist of those of British,
German, Irish, French, and other descents.  Those places have cultures
that should be celebrated.  Culture is not race based.

<p>The only culture that I could see as being in any sort of jeapordy
is that of the Germans.  (To some degree.)  It has gotten to the point
in Germany where waving a flag could get you labeled as a Nazi.  But in
the Americas, I don't see any such problem.

<p><b>White Heterosexual Male</b>
<br>Tacoma, Washington, Usa
<br><a href="mailto: "></a>

<hr>    

<h3><i>Stand up and be counted</i></h3>

<p><tt>Sat Aug 26 11:03 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>I'm writing this letter wondering where and when a person could attend 
a meeting with other people of this interest. Other groups in this country
have conventions, why not us? The problem with most people is that they 
don't want anyone really to know about how they feel or think. Damnit man
we still have freedom of speech and the right to assembly the last time I looked.
Come on join in, don't be ashamed the blacks have got NAACP and proud of it.
Let's hear more a organization. Post here.

<p>Thanks 

<p><b>THE HAWK</b>
<br>USA
<br><a href="mailto: "></a>

<hr>    

<h3><i>Identity Archaeology & Raymond Capt</i></h3>

<p><tt>Fri Aug 25 18:55 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>The Behistun Rock inscriptuion, and other stuff that is usually
cited to support Identity, is discussed by E. Raymond Capt in
MISSING LINKS or some such title, incl. refs. in title to
Assyrian records. I don't have it in front of me.

<p>Anyway, two points:

<p>(1) Capt never establishes that Khumri (for real Israel no 
question by authorities or anyone) and Kymry (Cimmerians) are 
the same, merely that they are simnilar enough sounding they
COULD be the same. A lot of peoples were dumped into the zone
between the Black Sea and the Caspian Sea and many were already 
there. Function: dumppes were to be buffers against those 
already there, for the Assyrians. There are radical changes
in language, order of words, physical culture, etc. to be made
in a scant 200 years if Identity is true. 

<p>To assimilate into the background peoples there, and to be 
their origin, are not the same things.

<p>(2) In Ezra and Nehemiah, lists of Judahite returnees are 
given, which are short by 11,000+ of the total figure of 
returnees given, which was specified as not including servants,
so that doesn't explain it. Also sacrifices were made for "all
Israel," a term used several times. NT mentions Anna of the
tribe of Asher present in Jerusalem at the time of Jesus'
birth. It is thought that the Israelite tribes' members who
were still interested in God were the extra ones.

<p>As for blood, remember John the Baptist condemned those who
counted on their physical descent to make them count, saying
that if God chose He could raise up sons of Abraham from the
stones.

<p>California
<br><a href="mailto: "></a>

<hr>    

<h3><i>Aryan Singles page</i></h3>

<p><tt>Fri Aug 25 02:50 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>Excellent idea by the previous writer. An Aryan singles column. I tried to write a letter on that subject and submit it a month ago but I guess it didn't get through. This web site is great. Makes us feel so not alone. I could possibly get the page started with the assistance of Mr. Black. Please E-mail me Don and tell me how we do this. Were are all the girls and women of Euro decent? If your a female and you have some friends who would be interested in participating in this page please E-mail and I'll set up some guidelines(with Don's permission of course) And to all you Aryan men, show these Women why white men are the best, be honest and noble. MDJ California

<p><b>MDJ</b>
<br>California
<br><a href="mailto: GvB_Hero@netcom.com">GvB_Hero@netcom.com</a>

<hr>    

<h3><i>Vit Makt!!</i></h3>

<p><tt>Thu Aug 24 17:10 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>I just returned to university from my summer vacation, only to find that, in order to get into the Net, I had to enter my name and the last four digits of my social security number. This applies to everyone who wants to use the computers. I asked the lab assistant, and she said that it's basically been done to monitor who uses what and who does what. 

<p>Not that I care if the university knows about my extra-curricular activities (I'm sure they do anyhow), but the very idea that they could monitor my activities on a day-to-day basis is intolerable. Of course, this type of tactic only makes me stronger. Now I understand how my brothers and sisters in more oppressive countries feel (as if there is any country more oppressive than the Jew.S.A). 

<p>My final thought: Don't let ZOG get you down. Stay strong and keep up the fight, for tomorrow does belong to us!

<p><b>Sylvia Rowe</b>
<br>Tennessee,USA
<br><a href="mailto: wa150%UTMARTN.BITNET@uga.cc.uga.edu">wa150%UTMARTN.BITNET@uga.cc.uga.edu</a>

<hr>    
  

<h3><i>Web site</i></h3>

<p><tt>Mon Aug 28 19:06 EDT 1995</tt>

<p>This web site is too cool. Keep up the good work!

