<p>An Aryan is a person of Indo-Hittite (Indo-European) ancestry. Germans, Kelts, Slavs (Russians), Kurds, Persians (Iran = Aryan), India Aryans, etc. are more or less pure Aryans. Not all "Whites" are Aryans. Semites (Jews and Arabs), Basques, Caucasians, and southern Europeans, etc. are part of a race which about 35,000 years ago emigrated from Africa to Eurasia, where they miscegenated with or exterminated the Neaderthals, before the Ice Ages. Glaciers cleansed northern Europe by pushing people south, which is why the pre-Aryans of Europe are referred to as the Mediterranean race, and why the Aryan race of Northern Europe (the origin of most "white" Americans) has remain pure enough to maintain the most powerful Aryan civilization. The ancient Aryan civilizations in the Middle East and southern Europe, once the most powerful in the world, have declined due to miscegenation with Mediteraneans.

<p>Aryan civilization was the first on Earth (in Canaan 12,000 years ago), and has led the world in science and technology ever since. According to the "History and Geography of Human Genes" (1994), Aryans (Indo-Hittites) entered Europe from the Fertile Crescent, and the Bible refers to Aryans as Hittites who are part of the Hamite (Canaanite) race, which entered Europe from the Sahara because of drought in the Sahel. The human animal is as savage as any other and also requires domestication (breeding out dangerous behaviors necessary to survival in a savage environment/society) before civilization can exist. Some races have not yet been domesticated.

<p>Would miscegenation be distroying the Aryan race if Aryan education began with a knowledge of Aryan racial identity, history, civilization, etc? Will life ever have access to the infinite resources beyond earth if the potential of Aryan civilization is not maximized by as pure an Aryan race as possible?

<p>I write this in the hope some of you who are reading this are fighters who will help to educate others about the need to preserve Aryan race/civilization and the science and technology which gives life the potential to colonize the Universe beyond this finite planet.

