<h3><i>Affirmative action</i></h3>

<p>Recently the Atlanta Journal/Constitution solicited our opinion on affirmative action. Below is the text of my letter:

<p>Affirmative action is a failure both to those it is intended to help and to those on whom the onus of mandated madness is imposed. You will always have the poor with you. Using police state tactics Russia spent 70 years trying to create a classless society. Such utopian dreams are in Plato's Republic and this scenario is acted out faithfully by our social insects but never by man, the free thinker.

<p>Our minority citizens, the Koreans, Chinese, Indians inter alios work and succeed in this society. Our African ex-slaves are ironically enslaved by the very social welfare system funded to help them. To further the irony businesses see them as a legal liability due to anti-business legislation. It is simply too dangerous to hire them because they can bring in the "feds" on any whimsical, fancied injustice. 

<p>The white man, be he employer or employee, is tossed into this egregious nightmare of balances and quotas. The employer faces a paperwork jungle of forms to be submitted; the well-qualified prospective employee may not get the job because of the numbers racket played by the E.O.E., etc.
In conclusion, affirmative action is an idealistic, unworkable doctrine of equality. Friedrich Nietzsche foresaw this more than 100 years ago. On equality he wrote: "There is no more poisonous poison anywhere: for it seems to be preached by justice itself, whereas it really is the termination of justice. Equal to the equal, unequal to the unequal - that would be the true slogan of justice; and also its corollary: Never make equal what is unequal."

<p><b>Dr. Adolf von Wurttemberg</b>
<br>GA
<br><a href="mailto: us003785@interramp.com">us003785@interramp.com</a> 

