<p><tt>Fri May 26 18:02:01 1995</tt>

<h3><i>Suggested Actions - Local Control</i></h3>

<p>Purchase a reliable firearm for every member of the family and learn
to use it.  It is necessary to have at least one completely legal
semi-automatic rifle or shotgun for use in cases of self-defense or
civil disorder.

<p>Second, be at least marginally respectful toward your local terror
police.  Buy the sheriff a cup of coffee if you see him at a resturaunt,
or give a friendly wave when you pass the state patrol. The rich man's
militia has the power to selectively enforce laws against us or against
our opponents.  They also serve as information gatherers for power
brokers in Washington and Tel Aviv.  The first step toward breaking
their hold lies in befriending the neighborhood cop, and voting for a
sympathetic boss in the next election.

<p> Anti-White facists in the Republican and Democratic parties are
gearing up for the 1996 corporate buy-out of Washington.  Both will turn
a blind eye to their past policies and attempt to cater to the emerging
body of armed patriots.  There also will be talk of greater anti-crime,
anti-terrorism, and anti-gun legislation to appease frightened liberals.
We'll have to eventually choose the lesser of a few evils, but we must
reserve our charitable funds and time for securing local control.  A few
hundred dollars and forty hours of work won't buy a plank on the
Republican platform, but it can tip the scales in a local sheriff's
election.
<p>There was a time when no jury in the South would convict a Klansman.
As our laws become more and more coercive, we need to return to the old
methods.  As we prepare for the 1996 elections, we should consolidate
local power by infiltrating police departments, befriending potential
jurors, and developing information networks - through radio, phone
trees, and email - that interpret news from a different standpoint than
our mass media.

<p><b>Terror-14</i></b>
<br>USA


