<title>Up Front 18--From the Front Desk</title>
<body>
<BODY background="images/upfront!bkg.gif">

<IMG WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=77 HSPACE=15 BORDER=0 ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="images/upfront!s.gif">
<center><IMG WIDTH=470 HEIGHT=6 BORDER=0 ALIGN=TOP SRC="images/gradlin2.gif"></center>
<br><br>
<h1>FROM THE FRONT DESK...</h1>

<p>In his recently-aired documentary, <i>Hearts of Hate</i>, film producer Peter Raymont stated, "There's a war being waged in Canada, a battle for young minds... Hard times, harder hearts have profoundly changed Canada. Many young people have lost hope 
of ever finding a job, or living as well as their parents."

<p>Sounded promising!

<p>Would he turn his lens on the treacherous and treasonous power-brokers on Parliament Hill? After all, he did promise to shine a
bright light into the dark corners of our society. Surely, there are no darker corners than the cavernous halls of power in Ottawa, where sinister decisions are made on a daily basis - decisions that affect the life of every Canadian on a daily basis, wh
ile they have little or no say in how their affairs are run. Decisions that will mean the ultimate destruction of the nation that our forefathers struggled to build.

<p>Of course, I'm being facetious. We knew damn well what this film was about. The evils of racism!

<p>If Raymont's intent was to make that Heritage Front look bad, he failed miserably. Cloistered away in his elitist cocoon, he failed to recognize the real anger and discontent that's out there.  Thousands of viewers who had suspected that we weren't qu
ite as evil as the likes of Bernie Farber have tried to portray us, suddenly got a chance to judge us without the usual System filters perverting the message. And they liked what they heard. The response has been overwhelming.

<p>Could we ask any more?
<p>
<PRE>                                            <i>Gerry Lincoln</i></PRE> 
<P>

