<head>
<title>Up Front 18--Hearts of Hate Review </title>
</head>
<BODY background="images/upfront!bkg.gif">

<IMG WIDTH=72 HEIGHT=77 HSPACE=15 BORDER=0 ALIGN=BOTTOM SRC="images/upfront!s.gif">
<center><IMG WIDTH=470 HEIGHT=6 BORDER=0 ALIGN=TOP SRC="images/gradlin2.gif"></center>
<h1>Love Your Race?</h1>
<h2>Then You've Got a <i>Heart of Hate</i></h2>

<strong>By Robby Vee</strong>

<p><i>Editor's note: When Peter Raymont's documentary aired on February
28th, we wanted someone to review it from at least arm's length,
someone who didn't appear in the film and hadn't even met the
producers. The hope was to minimize any bias, one way or the other.
Seventeen-year-old Robby Vee, one of our most promising young writers,
came through on a moment's notice. Hopefully, this is what the
average thinking White student saw.</i>

<p>What do you get when you throw together fifty-three minutes of
spooky background music, ominous-sounding narration, slow-motion
clips of street fights, and skillfully edited interviews with
Racialists?
<p>If you're a liberal supporter of the Establishment, you get yet
another entry in the seemingly endless parade of pseudo-documentaries 
attempting to discredit White Nationalists.
<p> But, if you're a Racialist, you get a nationwide advertisement for
people to join the Heritage Front.
<p> <i>Hearts of Hate: The Battle for Young Minds</i> aired on the last day
of February, a day I imagine many Racialists rue, as the film dwelt
on some of the seamier aspects of our movement. For one hour, the
viewer was treated to director Peter Raymont's droning alarmism, as
he recounted the movement's activities throughout the past few
years. Claims that White pride and love are really hate were
repeated ad nauseam, like some left-wing mantra. The film was
peppered with clever propaganda techniques, skillful cutaways and
a preoccupation with the isolated incident of violence that have
occurred - and always with provocation - from time to time.
<p> Did this slick System offering deal a dangerous blow to the
credibility of the Heritage Front and organized racialism?
<p> I don't think so. Not really.
<p> Personally, I think that such national media coverage, however
biased, with the potential of reaching every household in Canada,
is not a liability to the Front, but an asset. Seriously, could any
of us buy this kind of exposure? What began as a grassroots
articulation of discontent has just been presented to the whole
country! How many viewers watched, and said "hey, they're right!"
<p> Of course it would have been interesting to hear the full story
behind the Heritage Front, but I suppose petty details such as
truth are much too difficult for the left-wing media to deal with.
Nevertheless, one glaring omission stands out. Raymont skillfully
avoids pointing out the fact that it was the anti-racists who
incited the riot in Ottawa after the pro-White concert. What was
never shown was how the HF crowd had been goaded into retaliating
for hours before they finally were forced to take action to defend
themselves. Since Raymont had already assumed the anti-racists were
the "good guys" in this altercation, no doubt the fact that the
left-wing "ARA" outnumbered and began harassing the peaceful
contingent of Racialist is something that the viewing public
doesn't have to know.
<p> Mr. Raymont certainly has to repeat himself to convince us that
the Heritage Front is inherently violent. The shot of the Ottawa
confrontation is played twice in the program, and second time, the
ARA's Alicia Reckzin is heard saying, "once you kick someone in the
head for being Black, I don't think you can recover from that."
<p> Remarkable insight, Alicia, but you seem to forget that Graves is
White, as was everyone else involved in the melee on Parliament
Hill. And it was only scummy Marxist Whites who bore the brunt of
HF wrath outside Sneaky Dee's after they had trashed Gary
Schipper's home on June 11th.
<p>Both times the incident in Ottawa - actually only a few seconds
long - was shown in slow-motion, rendered in a surreal digital
gloss, with a low, eerie soundtrack accompanying the action. While
it makes sense from a propagandist's point of view to keep
repeating something that you want your audience to remember, one
must question Mr. Raymont's resources, or lack thereof. Surely he
could have found more examples if we're all just spoiling for
battle! After all, I am told that he was given complete access to
all recorded Front material by the Front itself.
<p>Unfortunately for the aforementioned ARA, Raymont does find other
examples of violence, but few indicating Racialists. The anti-
racists' cheap-shot vandalism of Gary Schipper's house is included,
and even though Raymont excuses this "raw street action" as taking
the law into their own hands, it is obvious that the ARA is far
more prone to hatred and violence than even the gruffest of
skinheads.
<p> <i>Hearts of Hate</i> doesn't spend much time explaining that when
Wolfgang Droege leapt into the subsequent College Street brawl, it
was to save the life of a young Front supporter who was being
attacked by a howling mob of bottle-wielding leftwing fanatics.
<p> True to his sensationalist industry, Raymont finds it more
important to lovingly describe the physiological details of
Droege's "assault" with gory musings on broken jaws and heavy
flashlights.
<p> In what we can only guess is an attempt at fairness, <i>Hearts of Hate</i>
allows several key Racialists to speak their views to some extent,
but it cannot resist interrupting them with narrative voice-overs
on how anything heard is actually a "racist myth," "bogus notion"
or that classic standby, "hate."
<p>As usual, the lack of arguments as to just why Racialism is so
invalid, are compensated for by plenty of name-calling and visual
effects. In one memorable segment, Raymont's elitism comes to the
forefront, as he refers to Wolfgang Droege's love of intellectual
freedom as "populist rhetoric of freedom of speech."
<p> Right Peter, why would anyone need to think for themselves, when
we have speech codes to tell us what is desirable and what isn't?
<p> The negative connotation added to the word "populist," which
normally refers to a political movement born of the common man, is
extremely revealing. It seems our "democratic" government can't
even keep its contempt for the Majority out of the very propaganda
aimed at the Majority.
<p> Fortunately, the charisma of our tireless activists shines
through. Though Raymont seems to delight in cutting off their
opinions in mid thought, what we do hear, especially from Droege
and Schipper, is rational and tempered, yet exciting and
passionate. Who could fail to admire - and agree with - Droege's
forthrightness when he said, "You may attack someone's house, but
you're not going to intimidate us. If someone seeks to harm me, or
commit violence against me, I don't think I want to turn the other
cheek."
<p> If the Left was trying to make the Heritage Front's leadership
look hateful and ignorant, it failed miserably! From the clips and
soundbites <i>Hearts of Hate</i> does afford our comrades, it becomes
abundantly clear that Racialism is on the side of the honest,
hardworking White Canadian, and that the government has lost all
touch with its subjects.
<p> No doubt the leftists are celebrating the many shots of Front
members giving the Sieg Heil salute. I can hear our enemies now:
What a shattering expose! How can the Heritage Front deny being a
fascist organization when such salutes are so commonplace?
 Well, an editorial comment in the March 1993 edition of Up Front
summed it up best. Such displays by young Front members are "merely
their way of expressing admiration for the only party in recent
history which put Race above all else."
<p> Sieg Heil salutes may not endear their presenters to the sellout
Establishment, but they undeniably give some factions of our
movement a sense of unity, cohesion and energy. I myself do not
apologize for any symbol, no matter how abrasive to mainstream
society, which serves to band together those who would fight for
their Race. If cries of "White Power" are too extreme for some
fellow Whites, well, they can go wring their hands with the likes
of the Reform Party or some other flock of weak little lambs.
<p>Yes, the Front has its radicals, its extremists, those who
understand only too well that if the System was just going to give
us back our land, it would have done so decades ago. If the rest of
White society wasn't so damned complacent, maybe we wouldn't have
today's problems of racial and national strife.
<p> In the holier-than-thou sanctimony that characterizes virtually
every media "examination" of White Nationalism, <i>Hearts of Hate</i>
loses any last shred of objectivity. Raymont makes no attempt
whatsoever to examine why Racialism is growing so strongly.
Instead, he contents himself with labelling all critics of racial
Marxism as ignorant savages. His film attacks White pride so
vehemently and without restraint that those not yet indoctrinated
by the Left must be wondering, "What is all the fuss about?"
<p>The truth is the System fears us because we are the only real
threat to its power, but the White masses, oppressed by crushing
over-taxation, ridiculous and suicidal immigration policies, not to
mention stifling political correctness, are just beginning to see
the light.
<p>Among the hundreds of thousands of viewers who watched Peter
Raymont's made-to-garner-sweeps-week-ratings effort, undoubtably
many of them sympathized with our struggle and question the
motives of the government and its minions in vilifying us.
<p>And thanks to <i>Hearts of Hate</i>, that light - however distorted by
Raymont's lens, just got a little brighter.

<hr>
<h2>Sometimes You Just Can't Win</h2>

<p>While many in the Racialist camp have been quick to criticize
Peter Raymont's made-for-TV effort <i>Hearts of Hate</i>, it didn't sit
too well with the leftists either.
<p>Dyed-in-the-wool liberal Joey Slinger, a mud-slinging, muddled-
thinking scribe who suffers from an unfortunate disability - he
actually believes people care what he thinks - whined that the film
was "pro-racist propaganda."
<p>He lamented that anti-racists are presented [in the film] as
"doddering goofs or hysterical urchins." Sounds like an accurate
portrayal to us.
<p>Slinger complains about the film's "lack of balance." Funny, he's
never worried about "balance" when writing his own left-leaning
drivel.
<p>A note at the bottom of his piece states:
"Slinger's column appears Thursday and Saturday."
... Why?

<P>
<hr noshade>
